73-5|location=Bloomington |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |ref=harv |date=2018|pp=874\u2013877|translator-last=Kramarikova|translator-first=Marianna}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia  |last1=Rajcan |first1=Vanda |entry=Poprad|editor1-last=Megargee|editor1-first=Geoffrey P. |editor2-last=White|editor2-first=Joseph R.|editor3-last=Hecker|editor3-first=Mel |series=Encyclopedia of Camps and Ghettos |volume=3 |title=Camps and Ghettos under European Regimes Aligned with Nazi Germany |isbn=978-0-253-02373-5|location=Bloomington |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |ref=harv |date=2018|pp=878\u2013880}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia|last1=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first1=Eduard |last2=Rajcan |first2=Vanda  |first3=J\u00e1n |last3=Hlavinka |entry=Sere\u010f|editor1-last=Megargee|editor1-first=Geoffrey P. |editor2-last=White|editor2-first=Joseph R.|editor3-last=Hecker|editor3-first=Mel |series=Encyclopedia of Camps and Ghettos |volume=3 |title=Camps and Ghettos under European Regimes Aligned with Nazi Germany |isbn=978-0-253-02373-5|location=Bloomington |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |ref=harv |date=2018|pp=881\u2013883|translator-last=Kramarikova|translator-first=Marianna}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia  |last1=Rajcan |first1=Vanda |entry=\u017dilina|editor1-last=Megargee|editor1-first=Geoffrey P. |editor2-last=White|editor2-first=Joseph R.|editor3-last=Hecker|editor3-first=Mel |series=Encyclopedia of Camps and Ghettos |volume=3 |title=Camps and Ghettos under European Regimes Aligned with Nazi Germany |isbn=978-0-253-02373-5|location=Bloomington |publisher=United States Holocaust Memorial Museum |ref=harv |date=2018|pp=889\u2013890}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Web====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Ghert-Zand |first1=Renee |title=First transport of Jews to Auschwitz was 997 young Slovak women and teens |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/the-first-auschwitz-transport-was-of-997-young-slovakian-jewish-women-and-teens/ |accessdate=4 Januar