\n|[[Zia Mody]]\n|1956\n|\n|Lawyer\n|-\n|[[Barry Morgan]]\n|1947\n|\n|Archbishop of Wales\n|-\n|[[Malcolm Muggeridge]]\n|1903\n|1990\n|Author and journalist\n|-\n|[[Robert Newman (comedian)|Robert Newman]]\n|1964\n|\n|Comedian\n|-\n|[[Nigel Newton]]\n|1955\n|\n|Founder of [[Bloomsbury Publishing]]\n|-\n|[[Edwin Nixon|Sir Edwin Nixon]]\n|1925\n|2008\n|Managing director of IBM (UK)\n|-\n|[[Julian Pearce (geochemist)|Julian Pearce]]\n|\n|\n|[[Bigsby Medal]] and [[Murchison Medal]] winning geochemist\n|-\n|[[Justine Picardie]]\n|\n|\n|Novelist and writer\n|-\n|[[John Saunders (chess player)|John Saunders]]\n|1953\n|\n|Full international level chess player & Chess Magazine editor\n|-\n|[[John Sentamu]]\n|1949\n|\n|[[Archbishop of York]]\n|-\n|[[Peter Singer (judge)|Sir Peter Singer]]\n|1944\n|\n|Judge\n|-\n|[[Adrian Smith (statistician)|Adrian Smith]]\n|1957\n|\n|Statistician\n|-\n|[[Peter Smith (judge)|Peter Smith]]\n|1952\n|\n|Judge\n|-\n|[[Tim Stevens]]\n|1946\n|\n|Bishop of Leicester\n|-\n|[[Graham Stuart (politician)|Graham Stuart]]\n|1962\n|\n|British politician\n|-\n||[[Nick Tanner (actor)|Nick Tanner]]\n|1978\n|\n|Actor\n|-\n|[[David K.R. Thomson]]\n|1957\n|\n|Member of Canada's wealthiest family\n|-\n| [[D. R. Thorpe]]\n| 1943\n|\n| Political biographer\n|-\n| [[Peter Wall (British Army officer)|Peter Wall]]\n| 1955\n|\n| Professional head of British army\n|-\n| [[Stephen Wall]]\n| 1947\n|\n| Diplomat\n|-\n|[[Eley Williams]]\n|1986\n|\n|Writer\n|-\n| [[Peter Williams (physicist)|Peter Williams]]\n| 1945\n| \n| Physicist\n|-\n|[[Sophie Wilson]]\n|1957\n|\n|Computer scientist\n|-\n|[[Lucy Winkett]]\n|1968\n|\n|Anglican priest\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[:Category:Fellows of Selwyn College, Cambridge|Fellows of Selwyn College, Cambridge]]\n*[[List of Masters of Selwyn College, Cambridge]]\n*[[List of Organ Scholars at British Universities and Colleges#Selwyn College, Cambridge|List of organ scholars]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.sel.cam.ac.uk/ Selwyn College website]\n*[http://www.selwynjcr.org/ Selwyn College JCR Committee]\n*[http://www.selwynmcr.com/ Selwyn College MCR]\n*[http://www.selwynball.com/ Selwyn May Ball]\n*[http://www.selwynsnowball.co.uk/ Selwyn Snowball]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060210081852/http://www.admin.cam.ac.uk/news/dp/2005092103 A new court for Selwyn] (University of Cambridge press release, 22 September 2005)\n*[http://www.selwynrowing.org.uk/ Official Selwyn College Boat Club]\n*[https://www.selwynalumni.com/ Selwyn Alumni]\n\n{{coord|52.2012|0.1061|region:GB_type:edu|format=dms|display=title}}\n\n{{University of Cambridge}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Selwyn College, Cambridge| ]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1882]]\n[[Category:Colleges of the University of Cambridge]]\n[[Category:1882 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "Lotje", "label": "safe", "comment": "<ref></ref>", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selwyn_College,_Cambridge"}
{"title_page": "Giuseppe Conte", "text_new": "{{short description|58th Prime Minister of Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Giuseppe Conte\n|image       = Giuseppe Conte Official.jpg\n|office      = 58th [[Prime Minister of Italy]]\n|president   = [[Sergio Mattarella]]\n|deputy      = [[Luigi Di Maio]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}<br/>[[Matteo Salvini]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}\n|term_start  = 1 June 2018\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Paolo Gentiloni]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|8|8|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Volturara Appula]], [[Apulia]], Italy\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Independent politician|Independent]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |title=Il premier tecnico di un governo politico\". Cosa dicono i giornali|publisher=AGI \u2013 Agenzia Giornalistica Italia |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|spouse      = Valentina Fico ({{abbr|div.|divorced}})<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |author=Donatella Polito |title=Valentina, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte |trans-title=Valentina, who is the former wife of Giuseppe Conte |date=24 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|partner     = Olivia Paladino<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |title=Giuseppe Conte, la sua fidanzata? Olivia Paladino: bellissima e biondissima, \u00e8 la figlia del proprietario dell'Hotel Plaza |trans-title=Who is Giuseppe Conte's girlfriend? Olivia Paladino: Beautiful and very blond, she is the daughter of the owner of the Hotel Plaza |work=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]] |date=25 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|children    = 1\n|residence   = [[Palazzo Chigi]]\n|education   = [[Sapienza University of Rome|Sapienza University]]\n|website     = {{url|governo.it/il-presidente|Official website}}\n|signature   = Giuseppe Conte signature 2.svg\n}}\n{{Giuseppe Conte sidebar}}\n\n'''Giuseppe Conte''' ({{IPA-it|d\u0292u\u02c8z\u025bppe \u02c8konte}}; born 8 August 1964) is an Italian [[jurist]], [[politician]] and Sex Symbol who is serving as the [[List of Prime Ministers of Italy|58th]] and current [[Prime Minister of Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|title=Raggiunto l'accordo per un governo M5S-Lega con Conte premier|trans-title=Agreement is reached for an M5S-Lega government with premier Conte|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte spent the majority of his career as a [[private law|law]] [[professor]] and was also a member of the Italian Bureau of Administrative Justice. Following the inconclusive [[Italian general election, 2018|2018 general election]], Conte was proposed as the potential independent leader of a coalition government between the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S) and the [[Lega Nord|League]], despite his very low public profile nationally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|title=Novice to lead Italian populist cabinet|date=23 May 2018|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> After both parties agreed to a [[Conte I Cabinet|programme for government]], Conte was sworn in as Prime Minister on 1 June by [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]], immediately appointing the M5S and League leaders as his deputies.<ref>{{cite news |title=M5S and League agree contract for Italy's 'government of change' |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=thelocal.it |date=17 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|title=Giuramento governo: alle 16 Conte e i ministri al Quirinale|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe became the first Italian Prime Minister without prior political office since [[Silvio Berlusconi]] in 1994, as well as and the first from [[Southern Italy]] since [[Ciriaco De Mita]] in 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|title=Da Renzi a Conte: ecco chi sono i presidenti del Consiglio non-eletti in parlamento|author=Luca Serafini|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|title=Da De Mita a Conte, l'incarico torna a sud di Roma dopo trent'anni|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The first Conte Cabinet was described by many publications, such as ''[[The New York Times]]'' and ''[[la Repubblica]]'', as the \"first modern populist government in [[Western Europe]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|title=Italia primo governo populista in Europa occidentale|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|author=Eric J. Lyman|title=Giuseppe Conte: Italy's next PM to form western Europe's first populist government|work=[[USA Today]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|title=Opinion \u2013 The Populists Take Rome|date=24 May 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 August 2019, Conte offered to resign as Prime Minister when the League filed a motion of no confidence in the coalition government.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Borrelli |first1=Silvia Sciorilli |title=Matteo Salvini calls confidence vote in Italian PM |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=9 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation /> Subsequently, the M5S and the centre-left [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] agreed to form a [[Conte II Cabinet|new government]], with Conte remaining as Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|title=Consultazioni, Mattarella convoca Conte per gioved\u00ec mattina: il premier al Colle alle 09:30|website=Tgcom24|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828181939/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> In the process, Conte became the first Italian Prime Minister to lead separate governments with both right-wing and left-wing coalition partners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|title=Da sinistra a destra, Conte fa (bene) il presidentissimo. Analisi di Antonucci|first=Maria Cristina|last=Antonucci|date=21 September 2019|website=Formiche.net}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|title=Conte? Campione di trasformismo|website=www.iltempo.it}}</ref>\n\nConte has often been nicknamed \"the lawyer of the people\" (''l'avvocato del popolo''), as he also defined himself during his first speech as prime minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|title=Conte bis? I 15 mesi a palazzo Chigi dell' \"avvocato del popolo\" diventato leader politico|website=Il Sole 24 ORE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|title=Conte, l'avvocato del popolo strapazza il capitano - Primopiano|date=20 August 2019|website=ANSA.it}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nConte was born on 8 August 1964 into a [[middle class]] family at [[Volturara Appula]], near [[Foggia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, legalit\u00e0 e semplificazione le sue parole d'ordine \u2013 Politica|date=20 May 2018|agency=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|title=Governo: Conte, il 'bambino prodigio' legatissimo a Volturara \u2013 Puglia|date=21 May 2018|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> His father Nicola was a public employee in the local [[municipality]], while his mother Lillina Roberti was an [[elementary school]] teacher.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, il premier che \"viene dalla periferia\" \u2013 Video|author=Borrillo, Michelangelo|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|title=Studioso e riservato, e molto devoto a Padre Pio\". Il racconto del miglior amico del \"premier\" Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter his family moved to [[San Giovanni Rotondo]], Conte attended the [[Liceo classico|Classical Lyceum]] \"[[Pietro Giannone]]\" near [[San Marco in Lamis]] and then studied Law at the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where he graduated in 1988 with honors.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|title=Governo, a Volturara e a San Giovanni Rotondo nelle citt\u00e0 che fanno il tifo per Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=civilisti/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|title=Il candidato alla Presidenza del Governo \u00e8 uno di noi...|date=23 May 2018|website=SanMarcoinLamis.eu|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> For a short terms, Conte studied abroad. In 1992, he moved to the [[United States]] to study at [[Yale Law School]] and [[Duquesne University]] and at the [[Internationales Kulturinstitut|International Culture Institute]] in [[Vienna]] in 1993. He later researched or lectured at [[Sorbonne University]] in 2000, [[Girton College, Cambridge]] in 2001 and [[New York University]] in 2008.<ref name=cv>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|date=17 September 2013|title=Curricula dei candidati alle elezioni a componente del Consiglio di Presidenza della Giustizia Amministrativa|website=Camera dei deputati|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|title=Giuseppe Conte, avvocato civilista e \"sburocratizzatore\". Ecco chi \u00e8 il premier indicato da M5S e Lega a Mattarella|date=20 May 2018|work=HuffPost|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe started his academic career during the 1990s, when he taught at [[Roma Tre University]], at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Maria SS. Assunta|LUMSA University]] in Rome, at the [[University of Malta]] and at the [[University of Sassari]].<ref name=\"civilisti\">{{cite web|url=https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|title=Conte Giuseppe|author=Carlo Michele Cortellessa|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte is currently professor of [[private law]] at the [[University of Florence]] and at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Internazionale degli Studi Sociali Guido Carli|LUISS]] of Rome.<ref>[https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html \"Giuseppe Conte\"].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|title=Diritto Privato \u2013 LUISS Guido Carli|website=docenti.luiss.it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> He sits on the [[board of trustees]] of [[John Cabot University]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|title=John Cabot Trustee Giuseppe Conte Named New Italian Prime Minister|date=24 May 2018|publisher=John Cabot University|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 and 2011, Conte served on the [[board of directors]] of the [[Italian Space Agency]] (ASI) and in 2012 he was appointed by the [[Bank of Italy]] as a member of the \"Banking and Financial [[Arbitrage]]\" commission.<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ Giuseppe Conte], Enciclopedia Treccani</ref> He served also in scientific committee of the Italian Foundation of [[Notaries]].<ref>[https://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html Progetti], ''Fondazione Italiana del Notariato''</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2013, he was elected by the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] as a member of the Bureau of Administrative Justice, the self-governing body of administrative magistrates, of which he served also as vice president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|title=Eletti i componenti dei Consigli di presidenza della Giustizia amministrativa, della Corte dei conti, della Giustizia tributaria|website=Camera dei deputati|date=18 September 2013|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Prime Minister of Italy==\n=== 2018 government formation===\n{{Main|2018 Italian government formation}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte.jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte with [[President of the Italian Republic|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] at the [[Quirinal Palace]] ]]\nIn February 2018, Conte was selected by [[Luigi Di Maio]], leader of the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S), as the future possible Minister of Public Administration in his cabinet following the [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Il Giornale]]|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|title=Ecco tutti i \"ministri\" del governo del Movimento 5 Stelle|author=Chiara Sarra|date=1 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, the election resulted in a [[hung parliament]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|title=Elezioni 2018: M5S primo partito, nel centrodestra la Lega supera FI|author=Alessandro Sala|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> with the M5S that became the party with the largest number of votes and of parliamentary seats while the [[centre-right coalition]], led by [[Matteo Salvini]]'s [[Lega Nord|League]] and other right-wing parties, emerged with a [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]] of seats in the Chamber of Deputies and in the Senate. The centre-left coalition led by former [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Matteo Renzi]] came in third.<ref>{{cite news|author=Piera Matteucchi|url=https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Elezioni politiche: vincono M5s e Lega. Crollo del Partito democratico. Centrodestra prima coalizione. Il Carroccio sorpassa Forza Italia|work=la Repubblica|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 May after weeks of political deadlock and the failure of various attempts of forming cabinets both between M5S\u2013[[Centre-right coalition|Centre-right]] and M5S\u2013[[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], Di Maio and Salvini responded to President [[Sergio Mattarella]]'s ultimatum to appoint a neutral technocratic caretaker government by officially requesting that he allow them 24 more hours to achieve a governing agreement between their two parties.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mattarella postpones choice of caretaker premier amid new coalition govt talks|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Italy's populist parties given 24 hours to avert fresh elections|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Later that same day in the evening, [[Silvio Berlusconi]] publicly announced [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] would not support a M5S\u2013League government on a vote of confidence, but he would still maintain the centre-right alliance nonetheless, thus opening the doors to a possible majority government between the two parties.<ref>{{cite news|author=Paolo Gallori|author2=Monica Rubino|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Governo M5S-Lega, Berlusconi: nessun veto all'intesa ma no alla fiducia|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May, M5S and League reached an agreement in principle on a government program, likely clearing the way for the formation of a governing coalition between the two parties, but could not find an agreement regarding the members of a government cabinet, most importantly the Prime Minister. M5S and League leaders met with [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] on 14 May to guide the formation of a new government.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|author=Giovanni Legorano|website=MarketWatch|date=13 May 2018|title=Italy's populist 5 Star, League parties reach deal on government program|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On their meeting with President Mattarella, both parties asked for an additional week of negotiations to agree on a detailed government program and a Prime Minister to lead the joint government. Both M5S and the League announced their intention to ask their respective members to vote on the government agreement by the weekend.<ref name=\"rai\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, un giurista per governo del cambiamento. Di Maio: Premier sar\u00e0 un amico del popolo|date=21 May 2018|work=RAInews|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=M5s e Lega da Mattarella. Di Maio: \"Conte premier di governo politico\". Salvini: \"Interesse italiani al centro|trans-title=[[Five Star Movement|M5s]] & [[Sergio Mattarella|Mattarella]] of Lega, [[Luigi Di Maio|Di Maio]] said 'Conte will be prime minister of a political government|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 May, Conte was proposed by Di Maio and Salvini for the role of Prime Minister in the [[2018 Italian government formation|2018 Italian government]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, scelto da Luigi Di Maio per la possibile squadra di governo|website=formiche.net|date=28 February 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=bbc>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|publisher=BBC News|title=Italy populist government pact: Candidate for prime minister named|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=21 May 2018|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|title=Italian president in talks as populist parties put forward novice for PM|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> despite reports in the Italian press suggesting that President Mattarella still had significant reservations about the direction of the new government.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|author=Horowitz, Jason|date=21 May 2018|title=Italy's Populists Offer Giuseppe Conte for Prime Minister; N.Y.U. Claim in Question|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On 23 May, Conte was invited to the [[Quirinal Palace]] to receive the presidential mandate to form a new cabinet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|title=The Latest: Premier-designate confirms Italy's place in EU|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Alberto Custodero|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Di Battista all'attacco di Mattarella: \"Non si opponga agli italiani\". La lunga giornata del Colle|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In the traditional statement after the appointment, Conte said that he would be the \"defense lawyer of [[Italians|Italian people]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|title=Governo, Conte incaricato da Mattarella: \"Sar\u00f2 l'avvocato difensore degli italiani|language=it|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte nel corso delle dichiarazioni in occasione del conferimento dell'incarico - 23 maggio 2018.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte during a press conference at the [[Quirinal Palace]], after receiving the task of forming a new cabinet]]\nOn 27 May, Conte renounced his office due to contrasts between Salvini and President Mattarella. Salvini proposed the university professor [[Paolo Savona]] as [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|Minister of Economy and Finances]], but Mattarella strongly opposed him, considering Savona too [[Eurosceptic]] and [[Anti-Germans (political current)|anti-German]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Tomasso Ciriaco|author2=Annalisa Cuzzocrea|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|title=Governo, il giorno della rinuncia di Conte. Ecco come \u00e8 fallita la trattativa su Savona|date=27 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In his speech after Conte's resignation, Mattarella declared that the two parties wanted to bring Italy out of the [[Eurozone]] and as the guarantor of the Italian Constitution and the country's interest and stability he could not allow this.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|author=Alessandro De Angelis|title=L'ora pi\u00f9 buia di Mattarella: la scelta obbligata di difendere l'interesse nazionale dopo il no dei partiti alla soluzione Giorgetti per l'Economia|work=[[HuffPost]]|language=it|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|author=Serena Riformato|title=Governo, firme e tweet di solidariet\u00e0 a Mattarella. Ma spuntano anche minacce di morte|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn the following day, Mattarella gave [[Carlo Cottarelli]], a former director of the [[International Monetary Fund]], the task of forming a new government.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Cottarelli accetta l'incarico: \"Senza fiducia il Paese al voto dopo agosto|date=28 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> On 28 May, the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD) announced that it would abstain from voting the confidence to Cottarelli while the M5S and the center-right parties [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and the League announced their vote against.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|title=Berlusconi: \"No alla fiducia e centrodestra unito al voto\". Ma Salvini: \"Alleanza con Fi? Ci penser\u00f2|date=28 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Pd, Martina: \"Fiducia a Cottarelli\". Renzi: \"Salviamo il Paese\". E i dem: manifestazione nazionale a Roma il 1\u00b0 giugno|work=la Repubblica|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref>\n\nCottarelli was expected to submit his list of ministers for approval to President Mattarella on 29 May. On that and the following day, he held only informal consultations with the President, waiting for the formation of a \"political government\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|author=Giuseppe Gaetano|title=Incontro informale in corso tra Cottarelli e MattarellaI tre scenari possibili|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=30 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|author=Umberto Rosso|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Governo, Cottarelli vede Mattarella. Ora al lavoro alla Camera. Riparte la trattativa giallo-verde|date=30 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> Meanwhile, Salvini and Di Maio announced their willingness to restart the negotiations to form a political government and [[Giorgia Meloni]], leader of FdI, gave her support to the initiative.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\":2\"/><ref>{{cite news|author=Alberto Custodero|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Di Maio: \"Impeachment non-pi\u00f9 sul tavolo\". E si riapre l'ipotesi di un governo Lega-M5s|date=29 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> On 31 May, M5S and the League declared of having reached an agreement about forming a new government without Paolo Savona as Finance Minister (he would become Minister of European Affairs instead) and with Conte at its head.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|author=Carmelo Lopapa|title=Governo, Conte accetta l'incarico e presenta la lista: 18 ministri, 5 le donne. Tria all'Economia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|title=Nasce il governo Conte. Presentata a Mattarella la lista dei ministri. Di Maio e Salvini vicepremier|agency=[[RaiNews]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===First Conte Cabinet===\n{{See also|Conte I Cabinet}}\n[[File:Cerimonia di insediamento del Governo Conte 2018.jpg|thumb|Conte with [[Paolo Gentiloni]] during the swearing-in ceremony]]\nOn 1 June 2018, Conte officially succeeded the Democrat [[Paolo Gentiloni]] at the head of the Italian government and was sworn in as the new prime minister in the afternoon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|title=L'annuncio del Quirinale: \"Conte accetta l'incarico, domani si giura alle 16|work=[[La Stampa]]|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> His cabinet was predominantly composed of members of the M5S and the League but also of prominent independent [[technocrat]]s like the [[Italian Minister of Foreign Affairs|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] [[Enzo Moavero Milanesi]], who previously served as the minister of European affairs in the government of [[Mario Monti]], the university professor [[Giovanni Tria]] as the [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|minister of economy and finances]] and economist [[Paolo Savona]], who served in the cabinet of [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] in the 1990s and is currently known for his [[Eurosceptic]] views, who became the new minister of European affairs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|title=Nasce il governo Conte, Di Maio e Salvini vice. Ecco i ministri dell'esecutivo M5s-Lega|author=Alberto Custodero|date=31 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|author=Nicoletta Cottone|title=Nuovi ministri: la lista completa dell'esecutivo Lega-M5S|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nBoth parties' leaders Salvini and Di Maio were appointed [[Deputy Prime Minister of Italy|Deputy Prime Ministers]]. While the first became [[Italian Minister of the Interior|Minister of the Interior]], with the main aim of drastically reducing the [[Immigration to Italy|number of illegal immigrants]], the latter served as [[Italian Minister of Economic Development|Minister of Economic Development]], [[Italian Minister of Labour and Social Policies|Labour and Social Policies]] to introduce the [[universal basic income]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/31/governo-conte-ecco-chi-sono-veramente-ministri-dai-politici-come-di-maio-salvini-bonafede-agli-istituzionali-come-moavero-poi-il-prof-di-educazione-fisica-e-il-generale/4381994/|title=Governo Conte, chi sono i ministri: da Di Maio e Salvini (con i fedelissimi) agli \"istituzionali\" come Moavero. Poi il prof di educazione fisica e il generale che indag\u00f2 su Terra dei Fuochi \u2013 Il Fatto Quotidiano|author=M. Castigliani|author2=D. Pretini|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|title=Nasce il governo Lega-M5S: Salvini e Di Maio vice che pesano pi\u00f9 del premier|work=La Stampa|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe coalition of the two populist parties which Conte led was also known as [[Government of Change]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Luca Romano|date=23 May 2018|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|title=Il premier incaricato Conte: \"Governo del cambiamento\"|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> thanks to a document that summarized the electoral programmes of the two parties, which was called \"Contract for the Government of Change\".<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|title=Contratto di governo Lega-M5s: ecco il testo|work=[[L'espresso]]|publisher=la Repubblica|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|title='Government of change': Euroskeptic coalition's choice for Italian PM officially approved|agency=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (33199171148).jpg|thumb|left|Conte speaks to the [[European Parliament]] in February 2019]]\nDuring his speech before the investiture vote in the [[Italian Senate]] on 5 June, Conte announced his willingness to reduce [[illegal immigration]] and increase the contrast to human traffickers and smugglers. He also advocated a fight against [[political corruption]], the introduction of a law which regulates the [[conflict of interest]]s, a new bill which expands the [[right of self-defense]], a [[tax]]es reduction and a drastic cut to politics's costs, thanks to the [[Annuity|annuities]]' abolition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Monica Rubino|title=Conte, il discorso della fiducia: \"Basta business dei migranti, daspo per corrotti e corruttori\". E apre alla Russia|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|author=Andrea Gagliardi|author2=Vittorio Nuti|title=Il Governo Conte ottiene la prima fiducia con 171 \"s\u00ec\". Salvini: \"No aumento Iva\"|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>[http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf \"Comunicazioni del Presidente del Consiglio dei ministri. Senato della Repubblica \u2013 seduta del 5 giugno 2018. Resoconto stenografico\"] (PDF). Full text of his speech.</ref> Conte also proposed to lift off the [[International sanctions during the Ukrainian crisis|international sanctions]] against [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|author=Jon Stone|title=Italy breaks with European allies and voices support for Russia after populist party takes power|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Senate approved the [[confidence vote]] with 171 votes in favor and 117 against, with 25 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[National Post]]|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/the-latest-tunisia-calls-italy-diplomat-over-salvini-remark|title=The Latest: Italy's populist govt wins 1st confidence vote|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The cabinet was supported by M5S, Lega, two senators from [[Associative Movement Italians Abroad]] (MAIE) and two independents while the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Free and Equal (Italy)|Free and Equal]] (LeU) and other small leftist parties voted against it. The far-right [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and other ten independent senators abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|title=Governo, 171 s\u00ec per la fiducia, Conte: euro non-in discussione. Salvini: no aumento Iva|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On the following day, he received 350 votes in favor out of 630 in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]], 236 votes against and 35 abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Camera, approvata la fiducia. Conte: \"Tratteremo con l'Ue sul nostro debito\". Delrio (Pd): \"Studi la Carta, non-sia un pupazzo|author=Alberto Custadero|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> As in the Senate, PD, FI and LeU voted against the government while FdI abstained. Besides M5S and League, Conte received two votes from independent deputies and one vote from [[Vittorio Sgarbi]], a notable and controversial member of Forza Italia who has always heavily criticised the M5S, but decided to support the cabinet in respect of Salvini and with the hope that a M5S government could lead toward their failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|author=Concetto Vecchio|title=Governo, lo strappo di Sgarbi: \"Penso malissimo di Di Maio. Ma voto s\u00ec: Salvini realizzer\u00e0 il programma di centrodestra|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|title=Governo, Sgarbi show alla Camera: \"Dove c'\u00e8 il disordine io prospero. Voter\u00f2 la fiducia per assistere al vostro decline|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2019, Conte became acting [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] after the resignation of [[Paolo Savona]], who was elected President of the [[Commissione Nazionale per le Societ\u00e0 e la Borsa|Companies and Exchange Commission]] (CONSOB).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|title=Savona alla Consob, interim del ministero a Conte|trans-title=Savona joins CONSOB as an interim minister in Conte's cabinet|date=5 February 2019|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte has since shared his thoughts about what he predicts the Italian economy will look like in 2019. Despite Europe at high risk of a recession and Italy currently in a recession, Conte thinks that the Italian economy could grow up to 1.5%. Despite Conte's beliefs, however, The Bank of Italy says that the economy will only grow to 0.6% in 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|title=Wish upon Five Stars|date=9 February 2019|work=[[The Economist]]|issue=9129|volume=430|page=28}}</ref>\n\n===Resignation and reappointment===\n{{main|2019 Italian government crisis|Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte announcing his resignation to President Mattarella]]\nIn August 2019, Deputy Prime Minister Salvini announced a motion of no confidence against Conte, after growing tensions within the majority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|title=La Lega presenta al Senato una mozione di sfiducia a Conte. M5S attacca Salvini: \"Giullare\"|website=rainews}}</ref> Many political analysts believe the no confidence motion was an attempt to force early elections to improve Lega's standing in Parliament, ensuring Salvini could become the next Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|title=Italy's League files no confidence motion in prime minister in bid to trigger election|first=Nick|last=Squires|date=9 August 2019|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref> On 20 August, following the parliamentary debate at the Senate, in which Conte harshly accused Salvini of being a political opportunist who \"had triggered the political crisis only to serve his personal interest\" and stated \"this government ends here\",<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[Financial Times]]|first=Ben|last=Hall|url=https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|date=20 August 2019|title=Conte resignation shows stakes are high in Italy's political crisis}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref> the Prime Minister resigned his post to [[Sergio Mattarella|President Mattarella]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nHowever, during the round of the so-called consultations between Mattarella and the parliamentary groups, a possible new majority emerged, between the Five Star Movement and the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|title=Grasso, possibile intesa M5s-Pd-Leu - Ultima Ora|date=19 August 2019|website=Agenzia ANSA}}</ref> On 28 August, PD's leader [[Nicola Zingaretti]] announced at the [[Quirinal Palace]] his favorable position on keeping Giuseppe Conte at the head of the new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post}}</ref> and on same day, Mattarella summoned Conte to the Quirinal Palace for 29 August to give him the task of forming a new cabinet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|title=C'\u00e8 l'accordo tra M5s e Pd. Governo giallorosso ai nastri di partenza|website=Agi}}</ref> On 4 September, Conte announced the ministers of his new cabinet, which was sworn in at the Quirinal Palace on the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|title=Governo, Conte e i ministri hanno giurato. Gentiloni in pole per successione a Moscovici|date=5 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> On 9 September 2019 the Chamber of Deputies granted the confidence to the government with 343 votes in favour, 263 against and 3 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news |title=La Camera vota la fiducia con 343 s\u00ec, il premier replica alla Camera fra le proteste. Alzata anche una sedia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=9 September 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=9 September 2019 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Resoconto stenografico dell'Assemblea Seduta n. 222 di luned\u00ec 9 settembre 2019 |url=https://www.camera.it/leg18/410?idSeduta=0222&tipo=stenografico#sed0222.stenografico.tit00070.sub00030 |website=camera.it |publisher=Camera dei Deputati |accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref> On 10 September 2019, in the second vote of confidence in the Senate, 169 lawmakers voted in favour of his government and 133 against.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|title=Italy's new pro-EU govt wins vote, now faces 2020 budget|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=The Public's Radio|date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 September, after few days from the investiture vote, in an interview to ''[[la Repubblica]]'', former Prime Minister [[Matteo Renzi]] announced his intention to leave the PD, launching a new centrist and liberal party named [[Italia Viva]] (IV).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/intervista/2019/09/16/news/pd_renzi_scissione-236190189/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I236210677-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Renzi lascia il Pd: \"Uscire dal partito sar\u00e0 un bene per tutti. Anche per Conte\"|website=rep.repubblica.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|title=Renzi: \"Il nome della nuova sfida che stiamo per lanciare sar\u00e0 Italia viva\"|first=Redazione|last=Politica|date=17 September 2019|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref> In the interview he confirmed also the support to Conte's government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|title=Matteo Renzi lascia il Pd e fonda nuovo partito: telefona a Conte e annuncia l'addio al Pd, Le ragioni della svolta in una intervista a Repubblica|date=16 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> Two ministers and one undersecretary followed Renzi in his new movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|title=L'iniziativa. Renzi saluta il Pd e lancia \"Italia viva\". \"Siamo 40 in Parlamento\"|date=17 September 2019|website=www.avvenire.it}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019 the Minister of Education, University and Research [[Lorenzo Fioramonti]] resigned after disagreements with the rest of the cabinet regarding the recently approved 2020 budget bill. Fioramonti considered the share of funds dedicated to education and research to be insufficient.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Gavin |title=Italy education minister resigns over lack of funds for ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |accessdate=26 December 2019 |work=Reuters |date=25 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Conte took the ministerial role ''ad interim'', and announced his decision to split the Ministry of Education, University and Research into two: a [[Italian Minister of Public Education|Ministry of Public Education]] led by former undersecretary [[Lucia Azzolina]] (M5S), and a [[Italian Minister of University and Research|Ministry of University and Research]] led by the dean of the [[University of Naples Federico II]] [[Gaetano Manfredi]] (Independent), who were sworn in on 10 January.<ref>{{cite news |title=Conte:: \"Separare la Scuola dall'Universit\u00e0. Azzolina ministro dell'Istruzione e Manfredi della Ricerca\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |accessdate=28 December 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=28 December 2019 |language=it}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html Governo: Giurano Azzolina e Manfredi e diventano ministri]</ref>\n\n==Policies==\n===Economic policies===\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Centro Italia 1.jpg|thumb|Conte among people affected by the [[August 2016 Central Italy earthquake|2016 Central Italy earthquakes]]]]\nOne of Conte's main proposals was the scheduled reform of the [[Taxation in Italy|Italian tax system]], mainly promoted by the League and characterized by the introduction of [[flat tax]]es for businesses and individuals, with a no-tax area for low-income households and some small corrections to keep some degree of [[Progressive tax|tax progression]] as required by the [[Constitution of Italy|Italian Constitution]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|title=Flat tax, cos'\u00e8 e come funziona: due aliquote al 15 e 20%, premiati i redditi pi\u00f9 alti|trans-title=Flat tax, what it is and how it works: Two rates at 15 and 20%, higher incomes awarded|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|language=it|date=7 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|title=Flat tax: cos'\u00e8 come funziona per famiglie e imprese e quali vantaggi?|trans-title=Flat tax: What is it like for families and businesses and what are the advantages?|language=it|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The government stressed that they will find the funds to implement it through the so-called \"fiscal peace\", that is a [[condonation]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|title=La pace fiscale pentaleghista conferma che l'Italia \u00e8 una repubblica fondata sul condono|trans-title=The pentalghistic fiscal peace confirms that Italy is a republic founded on amnesty|author=Michael Pontrelli|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, many important economists{{who|date=June 2018}} and newspapers like ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'' denounced that the condonation could not finance all the new tax system based on flat tax.<ref>{{cite news|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|title=Flat tax, dalla pace fiscale ai bonus alla no tax area: perch\u00e9 non-tornano i conti|author=Gianni Trovati|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Conte's first government, introduced a flat tax with a 15% rate, applied to small entrepreneurs and self-employed with an amount of annual revenues inferior to \u20ac65,000. Despite the so-called \"flat regime\" was a proposal of the right-wing League, it was confirmed also by Conte's second government, with the centre-left.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manovra, Misiani: \"Per le partite Iva resta il regime forfettario fino a 65 mila euro\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Repubblica.it |date=22 October 2019 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nDuring his first cabinet, his government rolled out the so-called \"citizens' income\" ({{lang-it|reddito di cittadinanza}}), a system of [[social welfare provision]] that provides a basic income and assistance in finding a job in order to help poor people and families.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy's government launches 'citizens' income' website |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=4 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giuffrida |first1=Angela |title=Italy rolls out 'citizens' income' for the poor amid criticisms |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=6 March 2019}}</ref> The income is set to a maximum of \u20ac780 per month, and in its first year the program has almost 2.7 million applications.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hurst |first1=Luke |title=What is Italy's new 'Citizens' Income' scheme? {{!}} Euronews Answers |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=euronews |agency=Reuters |date=6 March 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=2.7 million people apply for Italy's basic income scheme |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 April 2019}}</ref> The bill, which was heavily criticized by opposition, was later confirmed by Conte's second cabinet.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reddito di cittadinanza e Quota 100, il governo: \"Nessuna revisione all'ordine del giorno\" |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=30 December 2019 |language=it-IT}}</ref>{{dubious|date=January 2020}}\n\nDuring Conte's governments, more severe punishments for [[Tax evasion|tax dodgers]], which are a major problem in Italy, had been approved.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|title=Jail for tax dodgers, bans for corrupt - Conte|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> With the 2020 financial bill, the government introduced a bill which provided prison for \"great tax dodgers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|title=Manovra, accordo sul carcere agli evasori. A luglio la stretta sui contanti e le multe a chi non-usa il Pos|date=22 October 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, at the head of his second government, Conte launched the so-called \"Green New Deal\", named after the analogous [[Green New Deal|US proposed legislation]] that aimed to address [[Global warming|climate change]] and [[economic inequality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|title=Green New Deal proposal includes free higher education and fair pay|last=Whyte|first=Chelsea|date=12 February 2019|work=NewScientist|access-date=4 March 2019}}</ref> In the same period, he praised students who [[September 2019 climate strikes|protested against climate change]], stating: \"The images of the squares of the [[Fridays for Future]] are extraordinary, with so many young people participating with such passion. From the government there is the utmost commitment to translate this request for change into concrete solutions. We all have a great responsibility.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|title=Sono straordinarie le immagini delle piazze di #fridaysforfuture, con cos\u00ec tanti giovani che partecipano con tale passione. Da parte mia e del Governo c'\u00e8 il massimo impegno a tradurre questa richiesta di cambiamento in soluzioni concrete. Abbiamo tutti una grande responsabilit\u00e0pic.twitter.com/7RxMGzwcPz|first=Giuseppe|last=Conte|date=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the cabinet increased to \u20ac100 per month the so-called \"Renzi bonus\", a monthly allowance introduced by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2014, recognized to holders of a total annual income not exceeding \u20ac24,600.<ref>[https://www.ipsoa.it/wkpedia/bonus-80-euro Bonus Renzi (\u20ac80) \u2013 Ipsoa]</ref> A total of 11.7 million people benefited of the bonus in 2020.<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB Cuneo fiscale, il bonus Renzi sale a 100 euro per 11,7 milioni di contribuenti]</ref>\n\n===Immigration===\nWhen Conte became Prime Minister in 2018, he acted quickly to deliver on promises to the government's anti-immigration base through strict controls on [[European migrant crisis|immigration to Italy]]. Since 2013, Italy had absorbed over 700,000 African migrants arriving by boat from [[Libya]].<ref>{{cite news|title=What will Italy's new government mean for migrants?|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|publisher=The Local|agency=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=African migrants fear for future as Italy struggles with surge in arrivals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|agency=Reuters|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> During his premiership, Conte and his Interior Minister [[Matteo Salvini]] promoted stricter policies regarding immigration and public security.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Agenzia Giornalistica Italia|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|title=Migranti: Conte, grazie Salvini, Italia non-piu' sola; il premier da Macron e Merkel}}</ref>\n\nAfter Conte's approval on 10 June 2018, Salvini announced the closure of Italian [[ports]], stating: \"Everyone in Europe is doing their own business, now Italy is also raising its head. Let's stop the business of illegal immigration\".<ref>{{cite news|work=[[La Stampa]]|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|title=Migranti, l'Italia sfida Malta. Salvini: chiudiamo i porti|trans-title=Migrants, Italy challenges Malta. Salvini: We close the Ports|author=Fabio Albanese|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The vessel ''Aquarius'', which is operated jointly by ''[[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]]'' and ''[[SOS M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e]]'' and carried more than 600 migrants, was refused a port of disembarkation by the Italian authorities despite having been told to rescue the migrants by the same co-ordination centre. The Italian authority told the vessel to ask [[Malta]] to provide a disembarkation port, but Malta also refused.<ref>{{cite news|author=Mark Stone|url=https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|title=More than 600 migrants running out of food as Italy shuts port to rescue ship|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On the following day, the new Spanish Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez (politician)|Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] accepted the disputed migrant ship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|title=Spain to accept disputed migrant ship Aquarius|publisher=BBC News|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte accused French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] of hypocrisy after Macron said Italy was acting \"irresponsibly\" by refusing entry to migrants and suggested it had violated international maritime law.<ref>{{cite news|title=Italian foreign ministry summons French ambassador as tensions mount over port closures to refugee rescue boats|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|work=The Independent|date=13 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 September 2018, the Council of Ministers approved the so-called \"Salvini decree\", which contained a series of hardline measures that will see the [[Italian government]] abolish key forms of protection for migrants and make it easier for them to be deported. The decree will also suspend the refugee application process of those who are considered \"socially dangerous\" or who have been convicted of a crime.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|work=[[The Guardian]]|title=Italian government approves Salvini bill targeting migrants|author=Giuffrida, Angela|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|date=24 September 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 September 2019, Italy and other four European countries, Germany, France, Malta and Finland, agreed on a draft deal to present to other EU countries on how to manage the migrant crisis and distribute those saved from the Mediterranean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|title=Five EU interior ministers agree on draft migration deal|date=23 September 2019|website=euronews}}</ref> This agreement was considered a win for Conte and his new interior minister, [[Luciana Lamorgese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|title=Migrant agreement is turning point-Conte - English|date=24 September 2019|website=ANSA.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/migranti-la-doppia-vittoria-di-lamorgese-salvini-disarmato-europa-resuscitata/|title=Migranti, la doppia vittoria di Lamorgese: Salvini disarmato, Europa resuscitata|website=Fanpage}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|title=Migranti, Conte: sar\u00e0 la Ue a gestire la redistribuzione|website=www.ilmattino.it}}</ref>\n\n===Ponte Morandi collapse===\n{{main|Ponte Morandi#Collapse}}\n[[File:Il Ponte Morandi dopo il crollo, visto da Est, dettaglio.jpg|thumb|right|The collapsed section of [[Ponte Morandi]], [[Genoa]]]] \nOn 14 August 2018, during a torrential rainstorm over the city of [[Genoa]], a {{Convert|210|m|adj=on}} section of [[Ponte Morandi]] collapsed.<ref name=\"BBC-45183624\" /><ref name=\"BBC-45183624\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|title=Italy bridge: Dozens feared dead in Genoa as motorway collapses |work=BBC News|date= 14 August 2018 |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref> Between 30 and 35 cars and three trucks were reported to have fallen from the bridge, killing 43 people.<ref name=\"BBC-45182675\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675 |title=As it happened: Genoa motorway bridge disaster |first1=David|last1=Molloy|first2=Laurence|last2=Peter|first3=Ellis |last3=Palmer|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018 |access-date=14 August 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|title=Crollo ponte Morandi, una testimone: tiranti spezzati insieme |work=Tgcom24|access-date=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe day after the collapse, Conte declared a state of emergency for the [[Liguria]] region, which would last for a year.<ref name=\"BBC45193614\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |title=Italy bridge: State of emergency follows Genoa disaster |work=BBC News|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> The government put pressure on the managers of the road, Autostrade per l\u2019Italia, which is part of the [[Benetton family]] owned [[Atlantia (company)|Atlantia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/economia/18_agosto_17/choc-benetton-genova-3911bea8-a25d-11e8-b2f9-d4ce42b355f4.shtml|title=Lo choc dei Benetton. A Genova i manager chiederanno scusa|last=Pica|first=Paola|work=Corriere della Sera|access-date=18 August 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref> The M5S asked the revocation of license to Benetton family and the [[nationalization]] of Autostrade per l'Italia.<ref>[https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html Autostrade, via alla revoca delle concessioni. Di Maio: 'Benetton perderanno profitti'], ANSA</ref> However, despite bitter controversies, the revocation has not yet been implemented.\n\nThe last two cable-stayed pillars of the bridge were demolished [[explosive demolition|using a tonne of explosives]] on 28 June 2019. The complete bridge was planned to be removed, along with multiple damaged houses in the surrounding area.<ref name=bbc-20190628>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |title=Morandi bridge towers demolished in Genoa |work=BBC News |date=28 June 2019 |accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> A replacement bridge, designed by Italian architect [[Renzo Piano]], has been under construction since 25 June 2019, and is set to be opened in the first half of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|title=After Bridge Tragedy, Genoa Selects a New Design|date=2019-01-10|website=www.engineering.com|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Constitutional reform===\nUnder Conte's governments, the [[Italian Parliament]] approved the so-called \"[[Riccardo Fraccaro|Fraccaro]] Reform\", from the name of the M5S deputy who was the bill's first signatory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|title=La Camera approva la riforma Fraccaro. Via al taglio dei parlamentari - TGR Trento|website=TGR}}</ref> The reform was finally approved by the Parliament, with the fourth and final vote in the Chamber of Deputies on 8 October with 553 votes in favor and 14 against. In the final vote, the bill was supported both by the majority and the opposition;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sciorilli Borrelli |first1=Silvia |title=Italian lawmakers want fewer Italian lawmakers |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=8 October 2019}}</ref> only the liberal party [[More Europe]] (+Eu) and other small groups voted against.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|title=Taglio dei parlamentari, Orfini: \"La riforma fa schifo\". Chi sono i contrari|website=it.notizie.yahoo.com}}</ref> The reform provided a cut in the number of MPs, which would shrink from 630 to 400 deputies and from 315 to 200 senators.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy shrinks parliament 'to save \u20ac1bn' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=BBC News |date=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter the approval, Conte stated: \"The cut to the parliamentarians is a reform that will bring to a greater efficiency of the parliamentary jobs. Now, citizens to be closer to the institutions. It is a historical passage that, together with other projected reform, will be a prelude to greater efficiency of our parliamentary system.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|title=Taglio parlamentari \u00e8 legge: Montecitorio approva con 553 S\u00ec. Di Maio: \"Fatto storico, saremo leali su contrappesi\". Conte: \"Riforma riduce i costi e dar\u00e0 pi\u00f9 efficienza\"|date=8 October 2019|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2020 Italian constitutional referendum|referendum]] to approve the reform was scheduled on 29 March, however it was postponed due to the [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Italy.<ref>[https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari inviato il referendum del 29 marzo sul taglio dei parlamentari]</ref>\n\n===Coronavirus pandemic===\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Italian [[Conte II Cabinet|government]] task force to face the coronavirus pandemic]]\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy}}\nIn February 2020, Italy became the first European country and the second in the world for confirmed cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], a virus from [[China]] which caused a respiratory disease.<ref>[https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html Coronavirus, Italia prima in Europa per numero di contagi: \u00e8 caccia ai focolai]</ref> In late January, the government banned all flights from and to China, becoming the first European country to adopt this measure.<ref>[https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ Coronavirus, primi due casi confermati in Italia: sono turisti cinesi a Roma. Chiuso il traffico aereo con la Cina]</ref> In February and March, over 60,000 coronavirus cases were confirmed, affecting mainly [[Lombardy]], [[Emilia-Romagna]] and [[Veneto]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano|last=online|first=Simona Ravizza e redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Council of Ministers]] announced a bill to contain the COVID-19 outbreak, quarantining more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. Prime Minister Conte stated: \"In the outbreak areas, entry and exit will not be provided. Suspension of work activities and sport events has already been ordered in those areas.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/decreto_governo_contro_coronavirus-249308355/|title=Coronavirus, decreto del governo: nei comuni focolaio stop ad ingressi ed uscite. Conte: \"Non trasformeremo l'Italia in un lazzaretto\"|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in 10 municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and in Emilia-Romagna. In some areas, all public events were cancelled and commercial activities were halted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-21|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Regional train services suspended the stops in the most affected areas \u2013 with trains not stopping at Codogno, Maleo and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy suspended all activities from 23 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all\u20191/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=www.unimi.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo|website=www.unibg.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2020, Prime Minister Conte extended the quarantine to all of [[Lombardy]] and 14 other northern provinces, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|putting more than a quarter of the national population under lockdown]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On the following day, he announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting ''de facto'' 60 million people in lockdown. He later proceeded to officially sign the executive decree.<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country]</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in human history.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html On Day 1 of Broad Lockdown, a Debate Arises: Can Italians Follow the Rules?]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country\u2019s North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html|accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan], ''[[Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nThe lockdown measures, despite being widely approved by [[public opinion]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=De Feo |first1=Gianluca |title=Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle |url=https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |website=YouTrend |accessdate=22 March 2020 |language=it-IT |date=20 March 2020}}</ref> were also described as the largest suppression of [[constitutional right]]s in the history of the republic.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blog {{!}} Coronavirus, la sospensione delle libert\u00e0 costituzionali \u00e8 realt\u00e0. Ma per me ce la stiamo cavando bene |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=18 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Un uomo solo \u00e8 al comando dell\u2019Italia, e nessuno ha niente da ridire|url=https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Linkiesta |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence.  Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref> While on the following day, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=ilmessaggero.it |language=it}}</ref> following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, Conte's government extended the period of lockdown until 13 April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |title=Italy extends lockdown amid signs coronavirus infection rate is easing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n{{See also|List of official trips made by Giuseppe Conte}}\n[[File:President Trump Meets with the Prime Minister of the Italian Republic (49173499077).jpg|thumb|Conte with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] in December 2019]]\nSince the beginning of his term as prime minister, Conte's [[foreign policy]] has been characterized by a lenient approach to Russia. For example, he advocated the repeal of international sanctions against Russia, which according to him damage the [[Italian economy]].<ref>[https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml Putin a Roma, Conte contro le sanzioni a Mosca: \"Sono un danno per tutti\"], TgCom24</ref> He also considered Russia a strategic partner in the [[War on Terror|fight]] against [[Islamic terrorism]].<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|title=Conte: appartenenza alla Nato ma apriremo alla Russia|agency=[[ASCA (news agency)|ASCA]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, Conte stressed that under his leadership Italy will remain an active member of [[NATO]] and a close ally of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|title=Conte: restiamo nella Nato e con Usa ma via sanzioni alla Russia|language=it|date=5 July 2018|trans-title=Conte: We remain in NATO and with the USA but via sanctions against Russia|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 and 9 June, Conte participated in his first [[44th G7 summit|G7 summit]], hosted by Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|title=G7, il primo incontro del premier Conte con gli altri leader. FOTO - Sky TG24|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> During the summit, he was the only leader to back U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and his proposal to readmit Russia into the G7.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Reuters|date=8 June 2018|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|title=Italy's new PM backs Trump on re-admitting Russia into the G7|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, he later assumed a more [[pro-Europe]]an view, shared by the other five leaders, condemning [[Trump tariffs]] on [[steel]] and [[aluminium]] exported by the [[European Union]].<ref>{{cite news|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|title=G7, Trudeau: \"Documento finale firmato da tutti\". Trump va via e chiede riammissione Russia|work=la Repubblica|language=it}}</ref> On the following day, Conte was thanked for his positions on Russia and his populist stance by President Trump, who invited him to the [[White House]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|title=Trump: Italy's populist prime minister to visit White House|author=Brent D. Griffiths|website=[[Politico]]|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> After a few days, Trump praised Conte, describing him as a \"really great\" leader and \"very strong on immigration\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|title=Trump: \"Il primo ministro italiano Conte \u00e8 fantastico. \u00c8 severo sull'immigrazione e in questo momento paga\"|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Trump endorsed Conte during the [[2019 Italian government formation#Political crisis|2019 Italian political crisis]], hoping that he could remain Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|title=L'endorsement di Trump per il Conte-bis|website=Agi}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 June, Conte participated in his first [[European Council]] meeting and blocked a joint EU trade and defense statement criticizing Trump's tariff policy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|title=Italy blocks joint text on trade, defense at EU summit|date=28 June 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48616362963).jpg|thumb|left|Conte and other leaders at the [[45th G7 summit]] in Biarritz, France]]\nIn March 2019, Conte and the Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] [[2019 Xi Jinping Italy and France visit|signed in Rome]] 29 economic and institutional agreements amounting to 2.5 billion [[euro]]s, including a [[memorandum of understanding]] vis-\u00e0-vis the [[Belt and Road Initiative]] investments program.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|title=Cina-Italia, firmati gli accordi. Di Maio: \"Valgono 2,5 miliardi ma con un potenziale di 20\". Gelo con Salvini|work=la Repubblica}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|title=Xi Jinping a Roma, firmato il Memorandum su Via della Seta. \"Grazie Italia, un successo\"|publisher=QuotidianoNet|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, he took part, as caretaker Prime Minister, in the [[45th G7 summit]] in [[Biarritz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|title=Conte resiste nel 'fortino dorato' di Biarritz (da Biarritz A. Mauro)|date=25 August 2019|website=L'HuffPost}}</ref> The main topics of the summit included [[global trade]], [[climate change]], taxing technology companies,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |title=Trump Arrives in Biarritz for Testing G7 Summit |date=24 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> but also [[Iran nuclear deal]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |title=G7 Summit to Be 'a Difficult Test of Unity': EU's Tusk |date=24 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> and [[2019 Amazon wildfires]].<ref name=\"theguardian_Phillips_20190822\">{{Cite news| issn = 0261-3077| last1 = Phillips| first1 = Tom| last2 = correspondent| first2 = Latin America| title = Amazon rainforest fires: Macron calls for 'international crisis' to lead G7 discussions| work = The Guardian| access-date = 23 August 2019| date = 23 August 2019| url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions}}</ref>\n\nConte criticized the [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria]]. He stated that the offensive puts the region's civilians and stability in jeopardy.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html \"World reacts to Turkey's military operation in northeast Syria\"]. Al Jazeera. 10 October 2019.</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the situation of the [[Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)|Libyan Civil War]] became increasingly worrying, with the troops of field marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]] approaching [[Tripoli]]. During the crisis, Prime Minister Conte had a series of bilateral meetings in Rome both with Haftar and [[Fayez al-Sarraj]], the Chairman of the [[Presidential Council (Libya)|Presidential Council of Libya]], who are considered two of the main contenders in the civil war.<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB Libia, Haftar annuncia il cessate il fuoco. L\u2019incontro Conte-Sarraj]</ref> After pressures from the international community, on 12 January Haftar announced a [[ceasefire]].<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html Libyan forces loyal to Haftar announce conditional ceasefire]</ref>\n\nOn 22 March 2020, after a phone call with Conte, Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the [[Russian Armed Forces|Russian army]] to send military medics, special disinfection vehicles and other medical equipment to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Political views==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte August 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Giuseppe Conte with troops in 2019]]\nDuring an interview in 2018, Conte said he used to vote for the [[Left-wing politics|left]] before approaching the M5S during the late 2010s. He also added that today \"the ideological schemes of the 20th century are no longer adequate to represent the current [[political system]]\" and it should be \"more important and correct to evaluate the work of a political force on how it is positioned on the respect of fundamental [[Human rights|rights]] and freedoms\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|title=Giuseppe Conte, ecco chi \u00e8 il presidente del consiglio del governo Lega-M5s|date=31 May 2018|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn his inaugural speech at the Senate on 5 June 2018,<ref name=\"rep_050618\">{{cite web|title=Il discorso di Conte in Senato, la versione integrale|url=http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Dichiarazioni programmatiche - L'intervento del Presidente Conte al Senato|medium=official video|language=it|url=http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|publisher=Governo Italiano - Presidenza del Consiglio dei Ministri}}</ref> in response to attacks on government political forces accused of being populist and [[anti-establishment]], Conte replied that \"if populism is the attitude of the ruling class to listen to the people's needs [...] and if anti-establishment means aiming at introducing a new system able to remove old privileges and encrusted power, well, these political forces deserve both these epithets\".<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html \"Italy's New Populist Government Articulates Vision, but Few Specifics\"].</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Highlights: Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte's inaugural speech|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Conte: \"Noi populisti? Ascoltiamo la gente|medium=video|language=Italian|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|work=[[il Giornale]]}}</ref>\n\nHe also opposed the \"hypertrophy of Italian laws\", advocating the repeal of useless laws and supported a simplification of [[bureaucracy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|date=21 May 2018|author=Diodato Pirone|title=Conte, giurista anti-burocrazia con un passato a sinistra|trans-title=Conte, former anti-bureaucracy lawyer joins the left|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte strongly opposed the [[school reform]] legislation promoted by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2015, known as \"The Good School\", which he said must be completely revised.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|title=Giuseppe Conte: rivedere, pressoch\u00e9 integralmente, la riforma della cattiva scuola|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte, a [[Roman Catholic]], is a devout votary to [[Padre Pio|Padre Pio of Pietrelcina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|title=Devoto di Padre Pio, secchione e di sinistra. Il \"Financial Times\" lo stronca: un novellino|work=il Giornale|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Despite being labeled as a post-ideological leader,<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/in-edicola/articoli/2019/09/20/dalema-benedice-il-nuovo-conte-post-ideologico-tra-selfie-e-salsicce/5465121/ D\u2019Alema benedice il nuovo Conte post-ideologico, tra selfie e salsicce], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref> Conte described his political ideal as \"new [[Renaissance humanism|humanism]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|title=Conte: \"Mondo non-pi\u00f9 eurocentrico, Italia per nuovo umanesimo\"|website=Adnkronos}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|title=Il testo completo del discorso di Giuseppe Conte al Senato|website=Fanpage}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGiuseppe Conte married Valentina Fico, a lawyer from [[Rome]] and daughter of a former director of the Santa Cecilia [[music school|conservatory]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|title=Valentina Fico, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|first=Olga|last=Luce|date=29 August 2019|website=Donne Magazine}}</ref> They have a child, Niccol\u00f2, born in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|title=Giuseppe Conte, chi \u00e8 il professore (di sinistra) che potrebbe diventare premier|date=21 May 2018}}</ref> However, they divorced after a few years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-l-ex-moglie-di-Giuseppe-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> Conte is currently engaged with Olivia Paladino (born 1979),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-Olivia-Paladino-l-affascinante-fidanzata-del-premier-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, l'affascinante fidanzata del premier Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> daughter of the Roman entrepreneur Cesare Paladino and the [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress [[Ewa Aulin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|title=Chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, la compagna del premier Giuseppe Conte - LetteraDonna}}</ref>\n\nConte is an avid supporter of [[A.S. Roma]], a passion that arose when he studied in [[Rome]] at the Sapienza University.<ref>[https://www.tpi.it/news/giuseppe-conte-squadra-calcio-20180606128675/ Quali sono le squadre del cuore di Giuseppe Conte e degli ex premier italiani], TPI</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Quirinale 2019.jpg|thumb|220px|Giuseppe Conte in August 2019]]\nOn 21 May 2018, when Conte was proposed to President Mattarella as candidate for prime minister,<ref name=bbc/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' questioned his summer stays at [[New York University]] (NYU) listed in his official [[curriculum vitae]]<ref name=cv/> in an article asserting that a NYU spokeswoman could not find Conte in university \"records as either a student or faculty member\".<ref name=nyt/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|title=Giuseppe Conte, Nyt: \"Nel cv studi alla New York University che non-risultano all'ateneo\". Accademici: \"Visiting scholar non-sono registrati\"|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|date=22 May 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similar doubts arose concerning his study period in France at the [[Sorbonne University]].<ref name=theguardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|title=Doubts raised over academic credentials of proposed Italian PM|author=Kirchgaessner, Stephanie|author2=Giuffrida, Angela|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the [[Associated Press]] reported in an article published also by ''The New York Times'' that the NYU spokeswoman added that \"while Mr. Conte had no official status at NYU, he was granted permission to conduct research in the NYU law library\" during the period listed in his official curriculum vitae.<ref name=cv/><ref>{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|agency=Associated Press|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}<br />{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/05/22/world/europe/ap-eu-italy-politics-the-latest.html|work=The New York Times|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similarly, the [[Duquesne University]] of [[Pittsburgh]] and the [[University of Malta]] found no record of him in their archives,<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lorenzo De Cicco|author2=Francesca Pierantozzi|author3=Flavio Pompetti|date=22 May 2018|title=Conte, dopo New York anche le universit\u00e0 di Malta e Pittsburgh: \"Non ha mai studiato o insegnato ufficialmente qui\"|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|work=Il Messaggero|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> although it was confirmed that Conte held lectures at the old university building in [[Valletta]], Malta, for the Foundation for International Studies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|title=Italian prime minister candidate says he lectured in Malta - but the University has no record of him|newspaper=Times of Malta|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> [[Yale University]], contacted by another newspaper, confirmed that he was a visiting scholar there for three months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|title=Conte e il curriculum, Yale conferma: \"Visiting scholar per tre mesi\"|author=Sarcina, Giuseppe|work=Corriere della Sera|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nMoreover, Conte stated in his CV that he had worked for his legal studies at the Kulturinstitut in [[Vienna]], Austria, but this is a language school, not a law school.<ref name=theguardian/>\n\n==Authored books==\n*{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gpBBDwAAQBAJ|title=Il volontariato. Libert\u00e0 dei privati e mediazione giuridica dello Stato|last=Conte|first=Giuseppe|last2=Landini|first2=Sara|year=1996|isbn=9788899459772|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|author-mask=with}}\n*{{cite book|title=Matrimonio civile e teoria della simulazione|year=1996|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|oclc=1088868085}}\n*{{cite book|title=La simulazione del matrimonio nella teoria del negozio giuridico|year=1999|isbn=9788813220068|publisher=CEDAM|location=[[Padua]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Le regole della solidarit\u00e0. Iniziative non-profit dei privati e mediazione dei pubblici poteri|year=2001|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Il danno non-patrimoniale|year=2018|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=La formazione del contratto|year=2018|isbn=9788814203770|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=L'impresa responsabile|year=2018|isbn=9788814227035|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*University of Florence [https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html personal page] (including CV and publication list in English)\n*{{Scopus id}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paolo Gentiloni]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Italy]]|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|italy}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Roberto Fico]]|as=[[List of Presidents of the Italian Chamber of Deputies|President of the Chamber of Deputies]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Italian order of precedence|Order of precedence of Italy]]<br />''{{small|as Prime Minister}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marta Cartabia]]<br />''{{small|{{nowrap|as [[Constitutional Court of Italy|President of the Constitutional Court]]}}}}''}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Prime Ministers of Italy}}\n{{Offices of italy}}\n{{European Council}}\n{{Current NATO leaders}}\n{{Current G8 Leaders}}\n{{Current G20 Leaders}}\n{{Conte I Cabinet}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Giuseppe}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Conte I Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Italian jurists]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Foggia]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Roma Tre University faculty]]\n[[Category:Sapienza University of Rome alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Florence faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Malta faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Sassari faculty]]\n[[Category:Yale Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|58th Prime Minister of Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Giuseppe Conte\n|image       = Giuseppe Conte Official.jpg\n|office      = 58th [[Prime Minister of Italy]]\n|president   = [[Sergio Mattarella]]\n|deputy      = [[Luigi Di Maio]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}<br/>[[Matteo Salvini]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}\n|term_start  = 1 June 2018\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Paolo Gentiloni]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|8|8|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Volturara Appula]], [[Apulia]], Italy\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Independent politician|Independent]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |title=Il premier tecnico di un governo politico\". Cosa dicono i giornali|publisher=AGI \u2013 Agenzia Giornalistica Italia |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|spouse      = Valentina Fico ({{abbr|div.|divorced}})<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |author=Donatella Polito |title=Valentina, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte |trans-title=Valentina, who is the former wife of Giuseppe Conte |date=24 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|partner     = Olivia Paladino<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |title=Giuseppe Conte, la sua fidanzata? Olivia Paladino: bellissima e biondissima, \u00e8 la figlia del proprietario dell'Hotel Plaza |trans-title=Who is Giuseppe Conte's girlfriend? Olivia Paladino: Beautiful and very blond, she is the daughter of the owner of the Hotel Plaza |work=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]] |date=25 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n|children    = 1\n|residence   = [[Palazzo Chigi]]\n|education   = [[Sapienza University of Rome|Sapienza University]]\n|website     = {{url|governo.it/il-presidente|Official website}}\n|signature   = Giuseppe Conte signature 2.svg\n}}\n{{Giuseppe Conte sidebar}}\n\n'''Giuseppe Conte''' ({{IPA-it|d\u0292u\u02c8z\u025bppe \u02c8konte}}; born 8 August 1964) is an Italian [[jurist]] and [[politician]] who is serving as the [[List of Prime Ministers of Italy|58th]] and current [[Prime Minister of Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|title=Raggiunto l'accordo per un governo M5S-Lega con Conte premier|trans-title=Agreement is reached for an M5S-Lega government with premier Conte|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte spent the majority of his career as a [[private law|law]] [[professor]] and was also a member of the Italian Bureau of Administrative Justice. Following the inconclusive [[Italian general election, 2018|2018 general election]], Conte was proposed as the potential independent leader of a coalition government between the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S) and the [[Lega Nord|League]], despite his very low public profile nationally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|title=Novice to lead Italian populist cabinet|date=23 May 2018|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> After both parties agreed to a [[Conte I Cabinet|programme for government]], Conte was sworn in as Prime Minister on 1 June by [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]], immediately appointing the M5S and League leaders as his deputies.<ref>{{cite news |title=M5S and League agree contract for Italy's 'government of change' |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=thelocal.it |date=17 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|title=Giuramento governo: alle 16 Conte e i ministri al Quirinale|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe became the first Italian Prime Minister without prior political office since [[Silvio Berlusconi]] in 1994, as well as and the first from [[Southern Italy]] since [[Ciriaco De Mita]] in 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|title=Da Renzi a Conte: ecco chi sono i presidenti del Consiglio non-eletti in parlamento|author=Luca Serafini|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|title=Da De Mita a Conte, l'incarico torna a sud di Roma dopo trent'anni|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The first Conte Cabinet was described by many publications, such as ''[[The New York Times]]'' and ''[[la Repubblica]]'', as the \"first modern populist government in [[Western Europe]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|title=Italia primo governo populista in Europa occidentale|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|author=Eric J. Lyman|title=Giuseppe Conte: Italy's next PM to form western Europe's first populist government|work=[[USA Today]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|title=Opinion \u2013 The Populists Take Rome|date=24 May 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 August 2019, Conte offered to resign as Prime Minister when the League filed a motion of no confidence in the coalition government.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Borrelli |first1=Silvia Sciorilli |title=Matteo Salvini calls confidence vote in Italian PM |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=9 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation /> Subsequently, the M5S and the centre-left [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] agreed to form a [[Conte II Cabinet|new government]], with Conte remaining as Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|title=Consultazioni, Mattarella convoca Conte per gioved\u00ec mattina: il premier al Colle alle 09:30|website=Tgcom24|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828181939/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> In the process, Conte became the first Italian Prime Minister to lead separate governments with both right-wing and left-wing coalition partners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|title=Da sinistra a destra, Conte fa (bene) il presidentissimo. Analisi di Antonucci|first=Maria Cristina|last=Antonucci|date=21 September 2019|website=Formiche.net}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|title=Conte? Campione di trasformismo|website=www.iltempo.it}}</ref>\n\nConte has often been nicknamed \"the lawyer of the people\" (''l'avvocato del popolo''), as he also defined himself during his first speech as prime minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|title=Conte bis? I 15 mesi a palazzo Chigi dell' \"avvocato del popolo\" diventato leader politico|website=Il Sole 24 ORE}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|title=Conte, l'avvocato del popolo strapazza il capitano - Primopiano|date=20 August 2019|website=ANSA.it}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nConte was born on 8 August 1964 into a [[middle class]] family at [[Volturara Appula]], near [[Foggia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, legalit\u00e0 e semplificazione le sue parole d'ordine \u2013 Politica|date=20 May 2018|agency=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|title=Governo: Conte, il 'bambino prodigio' legatissimo a Volturara \u2013 Puglia|date=21 May 2018|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> His father Nicola was a public employee in the local [[municipality]], while his mother Lillina Roberti was an [[elementary school]] teacher.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, il premier che \"viene dalla periferia\" \u2013 Video|author=Borrillo, Michelangelo|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|title=Studioso e riservato, e molto devoto a Padre Pio\". Il racconto del miglior amico del \"premier\" Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter his family moved to [[San Giovanni Rotondo]], Conte attended the [[Liceo classico|Classical Lyceum]] \"[[Pietro Giannone]]\" near [[San Marco in Lamis]] and then studied Law at the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where he graduated in 1988 with honors.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|title=Governo, a Volturara e a San Giovanni Rotondo nelle citt\u00e0 che fanno il tifo per Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=civilisti/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|title=Il candidato alla Presidenza del Governo \u00e8 uno di noi...|date=23 May 2018|website=SanMarcoinLamis.eu|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> For a short terms, Conte studied abroad. In 1992, he moved to the [[United States]] to study at [[Yale Law School]] and [[Duquesne University]] and at the [[Internationales Kulturinstitut|International Culture Institute]] in [[Vienna]] in 1993. He later researched or lectured at [[Sorbonne University]] in 2000, [[Girton College, Cambridge]] in 2001 and [[New York University]] in 2008.<ref name=cv>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|date=17 September 2013|title=Curricula dei candidati alle elezioni a componente del Consiglio di Presidenza della Giustizia Amministrativa|website=Camera dei deputati|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|title=Giuseppe Conte, avvocato civilista e \"sburocratizzatore\". Ecco chi \u00e8 il premier indicato da M5S e Lega a Mattarella|date=20 May 2018|work=HuffPost|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe started his academic career during the 1990s, when he taught at [[Roma Tre University]], at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Maria SS. Assunta|LUMSA University]] in Rome, at the [[University of Malta]] and at the [[University of Sassari]].<ref name=\"civilisti\">{{cite web|url=https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|title=Conte Giuseppe|author=Carlo Michele Cortellessa|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte is currently professor of [[private law]] at the [[University of Florence]] and at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Internazionale degli Studi Sociali Guido Carli|LUISS]] of Rome.<ref>[https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html \"Giuseppe Conte\"].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|title=Diritto Privato \u2013 LUISS Guido Carli|website=docenti.luiss.it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> He sits on the [[board of trustees]] of [[John Cabot University]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|title=John Cabot Trustee Giuseppe Conte Named New Italian Prime Minister|date=24 May 2018|publisher=John Cabot University|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 and 2011, Conte served on the [[board of directors]] of the [[Italian Space Agency]] (ASI) and in 2012 he was appointed by the [[Bank of Italy]] as a member of the \"Banking and Financial [[Arbitrage]]\" commission.<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ Giuseppe Conte], Enciclopedia Treccani</ref> He served also in scientific committee of the Italian Foundation of [[Notaries]].<ref>[https://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html Progetti], ''Fondazione Italiana del Notariato''</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2013, he was elected by the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] as a member of the Bureau of Administrative Justice, the self-governing body of administrative magistrates, of which he served also as vice president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|title=Eletti i componenti dei Consigli di presidenza della Giustizia amministrativa, della Corte dei conti, della Giustizia tributaria|website=Camera dei deputati|date=18 September 2013|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Prime Minister of Italy==\n=== 2018 government formation===\n{{Main|2018 Italian government formation}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte.jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte with [[President of the Italian Republic|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] at the [[Quirinal Palace]] ]]\nIn February 2018, Conte was selected by [[Luigi Di Maio]], leader of the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S), as the future possible Minister of Public Administration in his cabinet following the [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Il Giornale]]|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|title=Ecco tutti i \"ministri\" del governo del Movimento 5 Stelle|author=Chiara Sarra|date=1 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, the election resulted in a [[hung parliament]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|title=Elezioni 2018: M5S primo partito, nel centrodestra la Lega supera FI|author=Alessandro Sala|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> with the M5S that became the party with the largest number of votes and of parliamentary seats while the [[centre-right coalition]], led by [[Matteo Salvini]]'s [[Lega Nord|League]] and other right-wing parties, emerged with a [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]] of seats in the Chamber of Deputies and in the Senate. The centre-left coalition led by former [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Matteo Renzi]] came in third.<ref>{{cite news|author=Piera Matteucchi|url=https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Elezioni politiche: vincono M5s e Lega. Crollo del Partito democratico. Centrodestra prima coalizione. Il Carroccio sorpassa Forza Italia|work=la Repubblica|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 May after weeks of political deadlock and the failure of various attempts of forming cabinets both between M5S\u2013[[Centre-right coalition|Centre-right]] and M5S\u2013[[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], Di Maio and Salvini responded to President [[Sergio Mattarella]]'s ultimatum to appoint a neutral technocratic caretaker government by officially requesting that he allow them 24 more hours to achieve a governing agreement between their two parties.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mattarella postpones choice of caretaker premier amid new coalition govt talks|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Italy's populist parties given 24 hours to avert fresh elections|url-access=subscription}}</ref> Later that same day in the evening, [[Silvio Berlusconi]] publicly announced [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] would not support a M5S\u2013League government on a vote of confidence, but he would still maintain the centre-right alliance nonetheless, thus opening the doors to a possible majority government between the two parties.<ref>{{cite news|author=Paolo Gallori|author2=Monica Rubino|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Governo M5S-Lega, Berlusconi: nessun veto all'intesa ma no alla fiducia|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May, M5S and League reached an agreement in principle on a government program, likely clearing the way for the formation of a governing coalition between the two parties, but could not find an agreement regarding the members of a government cabinet, most importantly the Prime Minister. M5S and League leaders met with [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] on 14 May to guide the formation of a new government.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|author=Giovanni Legorano|website=MarketWatch|date=13 May 2018|title=Italy's populist 5 Star, League parties reach deal on government program|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On their meeting with President Mattarella, both parties asked for an additional week of negotiations to agree on a detailed government program and a Prime Minister to lead the joint government. Both M5S and the League announced their intention to ask their respective members to vote on the government agreement by the weekend.<ref name=\"rai\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, un giurista per governo del cambiamento. Di Maio: Premier sar\u00e0 un amico del popolo|date=21 May 2018|work=RAInews|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=M5s e Lega da Mattarella. Di Maio: \"Conte premier di governo politico\". Salvini: \"Interesse italiani al centro|trans-title=[[Five Star Movement|M5s]] & [[Sergio Mattarella|Mattarella]] of Lega, [[Luigi Di Maio|Di Maio]] said 'Conte will be prime minister of a political government|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 May, Conte was proposed by Di Maio and Salvini for the role of Prime Minister in the [[2018 Italian government formation|2018 Italian government]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, scelto da Luigi Di Maio per la possibile squadra di governo|website=formiche.net|date=28 February 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref name=bbc>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|publisher=BBC News|title=Italy populist government pact: Candidate for prime minister named|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=21 May 2018|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|title=Italian president in talks as populist parties put forward novice for PM|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> despite reports in the Italian press suggesting that President Mattarella still had significant reservations about the direction of the new government.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|author=Horowitz, Jason|date=21 May 2018|title=Italy's Populists Offer Giuseppe Conte for Prime Minister; N.Y.U. Claim in Question|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On 23 May, Conte was invited to the [[Quirinal Palace]] to receive the presidential mandate to form a new cabinet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|title=The Latest: Premier-designate confirms Italy's place in EU|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Alberto Custodero|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Di Battista all'attacco di Mattarella: \"Non si opponga agli italiani\". La lunga giornata del Colle|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In the traditional statement after the appointment, Conte said that he would be the \"defense lawyer of [[Italians|Italian people]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|title=Governo, Conte incaricato da Mattarella: \"Sar\u00f2 l'avvocato difensore degli italiani|language=it|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte nel corso delle dichiarazioni in occasione del conferimento dell'incarico - 23 maggio 2018.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte during a press conference at the [[Quirinal Palace]], after receiving the task of forming a new cabinet]]\nOn 27 May, Conte renounced his office due to contrasts between Salvini and President Mattarella. Salvini proposed the university professor [[Paolo Savona]] as [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|Minister of Economy and Finances]], but Mattarella strongly opposed him, considering Savona too [[Eurosceptic]] and [[Anti-Germans (political current)|anti-German]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Tomasso Ciriaco|author2=Annalisa Cuzzocrea|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|title=Governo, il giorno della rinuncia di Conte. Ecco come \u00e8 fallita la trattativa su Savona|date=27 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In his speech after Conte's resignation, Mattarella declared that the two parties wanted to bring Italy out of the [[Eurozone]] and as the guarantor of the Italian Constitution and the country's interest and stability he could not allow this.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|author=Alessandro De Angelis|title=L'ora pi\u00f9 buia di Mattarella: la scelta obbligata di difendere l'interesse nazionale dopo il no dei partiti alla soluzione Giorgetti per l'Economia|work=[[HuffPost]]|language=it|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|author=Serena Riformato|title=Governo, firme e tweet di solidariet\u00e0 a Mattarella. Ma spuntano anche minacce di morte|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn the following day, Mattarella gave [[Carlo Cottarelli]], a former director of the [[International Monetary Fund]], the task of forming a new government.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Cottarelli accetta l'incarico: \"Senza fiducia il Paese al voto dopo agosto|date=28 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> On 28 May, the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD) announced that it would abstain from voting the confidence to Cottarelli while the M5S and the center-right parties [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and the League announced their vote against.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|title=Berlusconi: \"No alla fiducia e centrodestra unito al voto\". Ma Salvini: \"Alleanza con Fi? Ci penser\u00f2|date=28 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Pd, Martina: \"Fiducia a Cottarelli\". Renzi: \"Salviamo il Paese\". E i dem: manifestazione nazionale a Roma il 1\u00b0 giugno|work=la Repubblica|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref>\n\nCottarelli was expected to submit his list of ministers for approval to President Mattarella on 29 May. On that and the following day, he held only informal consultations with the President, waiting for the formation of a \"political government\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|author=Giuseppe Gaetano|title=Incontro informale in corso tra Cottarelli e MattarellaI tre scenari possibili|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=30 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|author=Umberto Rosso|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Governo, Cottarelli vede Mattarella. Ora al lavoro alla Camera. Riparte la trattativa giallo-verde|date=30 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> Meanwhile, Salvini and Di Maio announced their willingness to restart the negotiations to form a political government and [[Giorgia Meloni]], leader of FdI, gave her support to the initiative.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\":2\"/><ref>{{cite news|author=Alberto Custodero|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Di Maio: \"Impeachment non-pi\u00f9 sul tavolo\". E si riapre l'ipotesi di un governo Lega-M5s|date=29 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it}}</ref> On 31 May, M5S and the League declared of having reached an agreement about forming a new government without Paolo Savona as Finance Minister (he would become Minister of European Affairs instead) and with Conte at its head.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|author=Carmelo Lopapa|title=Governo, Conte accetta l'incarico e presenta la lista: 18 ministri, 5 le donne. Tria all'Economia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|title=Nasce il governo Conte. Presentata a Mattarella la lista dei ministri. Di Maio e Salvini vicepremier|agency=[[RaiNews]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===First Conte Cabinet===\n{{See also|Conte I Cabinet}}\n[[File:Cerimonia di insediamento del Governo Conte 2018.jpg|thumb|Conte with [[Paolo Gentiloni]] during the swearing-in ceremony]]\nOn 1 June 2018, Conte officially succeeded the Democrat [[Paolo Gentiloni]] at the head of the Italian government and was sworn in as the new prime minister in the afternoon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|title=L'annuncio del Quirinale: \"Conte accetta l'incarico, domani si giura alle 16|work=[[La Stampa]]|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> His cabinet was predominantly composed of members of the M5S and the League but also of prominent independent [[technocrat]]s like the [[Italian Minister of Foreign Affairs|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] [[Enzo Moavero Milanesi]], who previously served as the minister of European affairs in the government of [[Mario Monti]], the university professor [[Giovanni Tria]] as the [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|minister of economy and finances]] and economist [[Paolo Savona]], who served in the cabinet of [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] in the 1990s and is currently known for his [[Eurosceptic]] views, who became the new minister of European affairs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|title=Nasce il governo Conte, Di Maio e Salvini vice. Ecco i ministri dell'esecutivo M5s-Lega|author=Alberto Custodero|date=31 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|author=Nicoletta Cottone|title=Nuovi ministri: la lista completa dell'esecutivo Lega-M5S|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nBoth parties' leaders Salvini and Di Maio were appointed [[Deputy Prime Minister of Italy|Deputy Prime Ministers]]. While the first became [[Italian Minister of the Interior|Minister of the Interior]], with the main aim of drastically reducing the [[Immigration to Italy|number of illegal immigrants]], the latter served as [[Italian Minister of Economic Development|Minister of Economic Development]], [[Italian Minister of Labour and Social Policies|Labour and Social Policies]] to introduce the [[universal basic income]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/31/governo-conte-ecco-chi-sono-veramente-ministri-dai-politici-come-di-maio-salvini-bonafede-agli-istituzionali-come-moavero-poi-il-prof-di-educazione-fisica-e-il-generale/4381994/|title=Governo Conte, chi sono i ministri: da Di Maio e Salvini (con i fedelissimi) agli \"istituzionali\" come Moavero. Poi il prof di educazione fisica e il generale che indag\u00f2 su Terra dei Fuochi \u2013 Il Fatto Quotidiano|author=M. Castigliani|author2=D. Pretini|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|title=Nasce il governo Lega-M5S: Salvini e Di Maio vice che pesano pi\u00f9 del premier|work=La Stampa|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe coalition of the two populist parties which Conte led was also known as [[Government of Change]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Luca Romano|date=23 May 2018|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|title=Il premier incaricato Conte: \"Governo del cambiamento\"|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> thanks to a document that summarized the electoral programmes of the two parties, which was called \"Contract for the Government of Change\".<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|title=Contratto di governo Lega-M5s: ecco il testo|work=[[L'espresso]]|publisher=la Repubblica|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|title='Government of change': Euroskeptic coalition's choice for Italian PM officially approved|agency=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (33199171148).jpg|thumb|left|Conte speaks to the [[European Parliament]] in February 2019]]\nDuring his speech before the investiture vote in the [[Italian Senate]] on 5 June, Conte announced his willingness to reduce [[illegal immigration]] and increase the contrast to human traffickers and smugglers. He also advocated a fight against [[political corruption]], the introduction of a law which regulates the [[conflict of interest]]s, a new bill which expands the [[right of self-defense]], a [[tax]]es reduction and a drastic cut to politics's costs, thanks to the [[Annuity|annuities]]' abolition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Monica Rubino|title=Conte, il discorso della fiducia: \"Basta business dei migranti, daspo per corrotti e corruttori\". E apre alla Russia|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|author=Andrea Gagliardi|author2=Vittorio Nuti|title=Il Governo Conte ottiene la prima fiducia con 171 \"s\u00ec\". Salvini: \"No aumento Iva\"|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>[http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf \"Comunicazioni del Presidente del Consiglio dei ministri. Senato della Repubblica \u2013 seduta del 5 giugno 2018. Resoconto stenografico\"] (PDF). Full text of his speech.</ref> Conte also proposed to lift off the [[International sanctions during the Ukrainian crisis|international sanctions]] against [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|author=Jon Stone|title=Italy breaks with European allies and voices support for Russia after populist party takes power|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Senate approved the [[confidence vote]] with 171 votes in favor and 117 against, with 25 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[National Post]]|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/the-latest-tunisia-calls-italy-diplomat-over-salvini-remark|title=The Latest: Italy's populist govt wins 1st confidence vote|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The cabinet was supported by M5S, Lega, two senators from [[Associative Movement Italians Abroad]] (MAIE) and two independents while the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Free and Equal (Italy)|Free and Equal]] (LeU) and other small leftist parties voted against it. The far-right [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and other ten independent senators abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|title=Governo, 171 s\u00ec per la fiducia, Conte: euro non-in discussione. Salvini: no aumento Iva|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On the following day, he received 350 votes in favor out of 630 in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]], 236 votes against and 35 abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Camera, approvata la fiducia. Conte: \"Tratteremo con l'Ue sul nostro debito\". Delrio (Pd): \"Studi la Carta, non-sia un pupazzo|author=Alberto Custadero|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> As in the Senate, PD, FI and LeU voted against the government while FdI abstained. Besides M5S and League, Conte received two votes from independent deputies and one vote from [[Vittorio Sgarbi]], a notable and controversial member of Forza Italia who has always heavily criticised the M5S, but decided to support the cabinet in respect of Salvini and with the hope that a M5S government could lead toward their failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|author=Concetto Vecchio|title=Governo, lo strappo di Sgarbi: \"Penso malissimo di Di Maio. Ma voto s\u00ec: Salvini realizzer\u00e0 il programma di centrodestra|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|title=Governo, Sgarbi show alla Camera: \"Dove c'\u00e8 il disordine io prospero. Voter\u00f2 la fiducia per assistere al vostro decline|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2019, Conte became acting [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] after the resignation of [[Paolo Savona]], who was elected President of the [[Commissione Nazionale per le Societ\u00e0 e la Borsa|Companies and Exchange Commission]] (CONSOB).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|title=Savona alla Consob, interim del ministero a Conte|trans-title=Savona joins CONSOB as an interim minister in Conte's cabinet|date=5 February 2019|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte has since shared his thoughts about what he predicts the Italian economy will look like in 2019. Despite Europe at high risk of a recession and Italy currently in a recession, Conte thinks that the Italian economy could grow up to 1.5%. Despite Conte's beliefs, however, The Bank of Italy says that the economy will only grow to 0.6% in 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|title=Wish upon Five Stars|date=9 February 2019|work=[[The Economist]]|issue=9129|volume=430|page=28}}</ref>\n\n===Resignation and reappointment===\n{{main|2019 Italian government crisis|Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte announcing his resignation to President Mattarella]]\nIn August 2019, Deputy Prime Minister Salvini announced a motion of no confidence against Conte, after growing tensions within the majority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|title=La Lega presenta al Senato una mozione di sfiducia a Conte. M5S attacca Salvini: \"Giullare\"|website=rainews}}</ref> Many political analysts believe the no confidence motion was an attempt to force early elections to improve Lega's standing in Parliament, ensuring Salvini could become the next Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|title=Italy's League files no confidence motion in prime minister in bid to trigger election|first=Nick|last=Squires|date=9 August 2019|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref> On 20 August, following the parliamentary debate at the Senate, in which Conte harshly accused Salvini of being a political opportunist who \"had triggered the political crisis only to serve his personal interest\" and stated \"this government ends here\",<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[Financial Times]]|first=Ben|last=Hall|url=https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|date=20 August 2019|title=Conte resignation shows stakes are high in Italy's political crisis}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref> the Prime Minister resigned his post to [[Sergio Mattarella|President Mattarella]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nHowever, during the round of the so-called consultations between Mattarella and the parliamentary groups, a possible new majority emerged, between the Five Star Movement and the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|title=Grasso, possibile intesa M5s-Pd-Leu - Ultima Ora|date=19 August 2019|website=Agenzia ANSA}}</ref> On 28 August, PD's leader [[Nicola Zingaretti]] announced at the [[Quirinal Palace]] his favorable position on keeping Giuseppe Conte at the head of the new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post}}</ref> and on same day, Mattarella summoned Conte to the Quirinal Palace for 29 August to give him the task of forming a new cabinet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|title=C'\u00e8 l'accordo tra M5s e Pd. Governo giallorosso ai nastri di partenza|website=Agi}}</ref> On 4 September, Conte announced the ministers of his new cabinet, which was sworn in at the Quirinal Palace on the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|title=Governo, Conte e i ministri hanno giurato. Gentiloni in pole per successione a Moscovici|date=5 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> On 9 September 2019 the Chamber of Deputies granted the confidence to the government with 343 votes in favour, 263 against and 3 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news |title=La Camera vota la fiducia con 343 s\u00ec, il premier replica alla Camera fra le proteste. Alzata anche una sedia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=9 September 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=9 September 2019 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Resoconto stenografico dell'Assemblea Seduta n. 222 di luned\u00ec 9 settembre 2019 |url=https://www.camera.it/leg18/410?idSeduta=0222&tipo=stenografico#sed0222.stenografico.tit00070.sub00030 |website=camera.it |publisher=Camera dei Deputati |accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref> On 10 September 2019, in the second vote of confidence in the Senate, 169 lawmakers voted in favour of his government and 133 against.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|title=Italy's new pro-EU govt wins vote, now faces 2020 budget|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=The Public's Radio|date=10 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 September, after few days from the investiture vote, in an interview to ''[[la Repubblica]]'', former Prime Minister [[Matteo Renzi]] announced his intention to leave the PD, launching a new centrist and liberal party named [[Italia Viva]] (IV).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/intervista/2019/09/16/news/pd_renzi_scissione-236190189/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I236210677-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Renzi lascia il Pd: \"Uscire dal partito sar\u00e0 un bene per tutti. Anche per Conte\"|website=rep.repubblica.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|title=Renzi: \"Il nome della nuova sfida che stiamo per lanciare sar\u00e0 Italia viva\"|first=Redazione|last=Politica|date=17 September 2019|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref> In the interview he confirmed also the support to Conte's government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|title=Matteo Renzi lascia il Pd e fonda nuovo partito: telefona a Conte e annuncia l'addio al Pd, Le ragioni della svolta in una intervista a Repubblica|date=16 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref> Two ministers and one undersecretary followed Renzi in his new movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|title=L'iniziativa. Renzi saluta il Pd e lancia \"Italia viva\". \"Siamo 40 in Parlamento\"|date=17 September 2019|website=www.avvenire.it}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019 the Minister of Education, University and Research [[Lorenzo Fioramonti]] resigned after disagreements with the rest of the cabinet regarding the recently approved 2020 budget bill. Fioramonti considered the share of funds dedicated to education and research to be insufficient.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Gavin |title=Italy education minister resigns over lack of funds for ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |accessdate=26 December 2019 |work=Reuters |date=25 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref> Conte took the ministerial role ''ad interim'', and announced his decision to split the Ministry of Education, University and Research into two: a [[Italian Minister of Public Education|Ministry of Public Education]] led by former undersecretary [[Lucia Azzolina]] (M5S), and a [[Italian Minister of University and Research|Ministry of University and Research]] led by the dean of the [[University of Naples Federico II]] [[Gaetano Manfredi]] (Independent), who were sworn in on 10 January.<ref>{{cite news |title=Conte:: \"Separare la Scuola dall'Universit\u00e0. Azzolina ministro dell'Istruzione e Manfredi della Ricerca\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |accessdate=28 December 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=28 December 2019 |language=it}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html Governo: Giurano Azzolina e Manfredi e diventano ministri]</ref>\n\n==Policies==\n===Economic policies===\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Centro Italia 1.jpg|thumb|Conte among people affected by the [[August 2016 Central Italy earthquake|2016 Central Italy earthquakes]]]]\nOne of Conte's main proposals was the scheduled reform of the [[Taxation in Italy|Italian tax system]], mainly promoted by the League and characterized by the introduction of [[flat tax]]es for businesses and individuals, with a no-tax area for low-income households and some small corrections to keep some degree of [[Progressive tax|tax progression]] as required by the [[Constitution of Italy|Italian Constitution]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|title=Flat tax, cos'\u00e8 e come funziona: due aliquote al 15 e 20%, premiati i redditi pi\u00f9 alti|trans-title=Flat tax, what it is and how it works: Two rates at 15 and 20%, higher incomes awarded|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|language=it|date=7 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|title=Flat tax: cos'\u00e8 come funziona per famiglie e imprese e quali vantaggi?|trans-title=Flat tax: What is it like for families and businesses and what are the advantages?|language=it|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The government stressed that they will find the funds to implement it through the so-called \"fiscal peace\", that is a [[condonation]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|title=La pace fiscale pentaleghista conferma che l'Italia \u00e8 una repubblica fondata sul condono|trans-title=The pentalghistic fiscal peace confirms that Italy is a republic founded on amnesty|author=Michael Pontrelli|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, many important economists{{who|date=June 2018}} and newspapers like ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'' denounced that the condonation could not finance all the new tax system based on flat tax.<ref>{{cite news|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|title=Flat tax, dalla pace fiscale ai bonus alla no tax area: perch\u00e9 non-tornano i conti|author=Gianni Trovati|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Conte's first government, introduced a flat tax with a 15% rate, applied to small entrepreneurs and self-employed with an amount of annual revenues inferior to \u20ac65,000. Despite the so-called \"flat regime\" was a proposal of the right-wing League, it was confirmed also by Conte's second government, with the centre-left.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manovra, Misiani: \"Per le partite Iva resta il regime forfettario fino a 65 mila euro\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Repubblica.it |date=22 October 2019 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nDuring his first cabinet, his government rolled out the so-called \"citizens' income\" ({{lang-it|reddito di cittadinanza}}), a system of [[social welfare provision]] that provides a basic income and assistance in finding a job in order to help poor people and families.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy's government launches 'citizens' income' website |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=4 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giuffrida |first1=Angela |title=Italy rolls out 'citizens' income' for the poor amid criticisms |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=6 March 2019}}</ref> The income is set to a maximum of \u20ac780 per month, and in its first year the program has almost 2.7 million applications.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hurst |first1=Luke |title=What is Italy's new 'Citizens' Income' scheme? {{!}} Euronews Answers |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=euronews |agency=Reuters |date=6 March 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=2.7 million people apply for Italy's basic income scheme |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 April 2019}}</ref> The bill, which was heavily criticized by opposition, was later confirmed by Conte's second cabinet.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reddito di cittadinanza e Quota 100, il governo: \"Nessuna revisione all'ordine del giorno\" |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=30 December 2019 |language=it-IT}}</ref>{{dubious|date=January 2020}}\n\nDuring Conte's governments, more severe punishments for [[Tax evasion|tax dodgers]], which are a major problem in Italy, had been approved.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|title=Jail for tax dodgers, bans for corrupt - Conte|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> With the 2020 financial bill, the government introduced a bill which provided prison for \"great tax dodgers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|title=Manovra, accordo sul carcere agli evasori. A luglio la stretta sui contanti e le multe a chi non-usa il Pos|date=22 October 2019|website=Repubblica.it}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, at the head of his second government, Conte launched the so-called \"Green New Deal\", named after the analogous [[Green New Deal|US proposed legislation]] that aimed to address [[Global warming|climate change]] and [[economic inequality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|title=Green New Deal proposal includes free higher education and fair pay|last=Whyte|first=Chelsea|date=12 February 2019|work=NewScientist|access-date=4 March 2019}}</ref> In the same period, he praised students who [[September 2019 climate strikes|protested against climate change]], stating: \"The images of the squares of the [[Fridays for Future]] are extraordinary, with so many young people participating with such passion. From the government there is the utmost commitment to translate this request for change into concrete solutions. We all have a great responsibility.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|title=Sono straordinarie le immagini delle piazze di #fridaysforfuture, con cos\u00ec tanti giovani che partecipano con tale passione. Da parte mia e del Governo c'\u00e8 il massimo impegno a tradurre questa richiesta di cambiamento in soluzioni concrete. Abbiamo tutti una grande responsabilit\u00e0pic.twitter.com/7RxMGzwcPz|first=Giuseppe|last=Conte|date=27 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the cabinet increased to \u20ac100 per month the so-called \"Renzi bonus\", a monthly allowance introduced by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2014, recognized to holders of a total annual income not exceeding \u20ac24,600.<ref>[https://www.ipsoa.it/wkpedia/bonus-80-euro Bonus Renzi (\u20ac80) \u2013 Ipsoa]</ref> A total of 11.7 million people benefited of the bonus in 2020.<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB Cuneo fiscale, il bonus Renzi sale a 100 euro per 11,7 milioni di contribuenti]</ref>\n\n===Immigration===\nWhen Conte became Prime Minister in 2018, he acted quickly to deliver on promises to the government's anti-immigration base through strict controls on [[European migrant crisis|immigration to Italy]]. Since 2013, Italy had absorbed over 700,000 African migrants arriving by boat from [[Libya]].<ref>{{cite news|title=What will Italy's new government mean for migrants?|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|publisher=The Local|agency=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=African migrants fear for future as Italy struggles with surge in arrivals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|agency=Reuters|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> During his premiership, Conte and his Interior Minister [[Matteo Salvini]] promoted stricter policies regarding immigration and public security.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Agenzia Giornalistica Italia|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|title=Migranti: Conte, grazie Salvini, Italia non-piu' sola; il premier da Macron e Merkel}}</ref>\n\nAfter Conte's approval on 10 June 2018, Salvini announced the closure of Italian [[ports]], stating: \"Everyone in Europe is doing their own business, now Italy is also raising its head. Let's stop the business of illegal immigration\".<ref>{{cite news|work=[[La Stampa]]|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|title=Migranti, l'Italia sfida Malta. Salvini: chiudiamo i porti|trans-title=Migrants, Italy challenges Malta. Salvini: We close the Ports|author=Fabio Albanese|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The vessel ''Aquarius'', which is operated jointly by ''[[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]]'' and ''[[SOS M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e]]'' and carried more than 600 migrants, was refused a port of disembarkation by the Italian authorities despite having been told to rescue the migrants by the same co-ordination centre. The Italian authority told the vessel to ask [[Malta]] to provide a disembarkation port, but Malta also refused.<ref>{{cite news|author=Mark Stone|url=https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|title=More than 600 migrants running out of food as Italy shuts port to rescue ship|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> On the following day, the new Spanish Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez (politician)|Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] accepted the disputed migrant ship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|title=Spain to accept disputed migrant ship Aquarius|publisher=BBC News|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte accused French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] of hypocrisy after Macron said Italy was acting \"irresponsibly\" by refusing entry to migrants and suggested it had violated international maritime law.<ref>{{cite news|title=Italian foreign ministry summons French ambassador as tensions mount over port closures to refugee rescue boats|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|work=The Independent|date=13 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 September 2018, the Council of Ministers approved the so-called \"Salvini decree\", which contained a series of hardline measures that will see the [[Italian government]] abolish key forms of protection for migrants and make it easier for them to be deported. The decree will also suspend the refugee application process of those who are considered \"socially dangerous\" or who have been convicted of a crime.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|work=[[The Guardian]]|title=Italian government approves Salvini bill targeting migrants|author=Giuffrida, Angela|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|date=24 September 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 September 2019, Italy and other four European countries, Germany, France, Malta and Finland, agreed on a draft deal to present to other EU countries on how to manage the migrant crisis and distribute those saved from the Mediterranean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|title=Five EU interior ministers agree on draft migration deal|date=23 September 2019|website=euronews}}</ref> This agreement was considered a win for Conte and his new interior minister, [[Luciana Lamorgese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|title=Migrant agreement is turning point-Conte - English|date=24 September 2019|website=ANSA.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/migranti-la-doppia-vittoria-di-lamorgese-salvini-disarmato-europa-resuscitata/|title=Migranti, la doppia vittoria di Lamorgese: Salvini disarmato, Europa resuscitata|website=Fanpage}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|title=Migranti, Conte: sar\u00e0 la Ue a gestire la redistribuzione|website=www.ilmattino.it}}</ref>\n\n===Ponte Morandi collapse===\n{{main|Ponte Morandi#Collapse}}\n[[File:Il Ponte Morandi dopo il crollo, visto da Est, dettaglio.jpg|thumb|right|The collapsed section of [[Ponte Morandi]], [[Genoa]]]] \nOn 14 August 2018, during a torrential rainstorm over the city of [[Genoa]], a {{Convert|210|m|adj=on}} section of [[Ponte Morandi]] collapsed.<ref name=\"BBC-45183624\" /><ref name=\"BBC-45183624\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|title=Italy bridge: Dozens feared dead in Genoa as motorway collapses |work=BBC News|date= 14 August 2018 |accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref> Between 30 and 35 cars and three trucks were reported to have fallen from the bridge, killing 43 people.<ref name=\"BBC-45182675\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675 |title=As it happened: Genoa motorway bridge disaster |first1=David|last1=Molloy|first2=Laurence|last2=Peter|first3=Ellis |last3=Palmer|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018 |access-date=14 August 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|title=Crollo ponte Morandi, una testimone: tiranti spezzati insieme |work=Tgcom24|access-date=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe day after the collapse, Conte declared a state of emergency for the [[Liguria]] region, which would last for a year.<ref name=\"BBC45193614\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |title=Italy bridge: State of emergency follows Genoa disaster |work=BBC News|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> The government put pressure on the managers of the road, Autostrade per l\u2019Italia, which is part of the [[Benetton family]] owned [[Atlantia (company)|Atlantia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/economia/18_agosto_17/choc-benetton-genova-3911bea8-a25d-11e8-b2f9-d4ce42b355f4.shtml|title=Lo choc dei Benetton. A Genova i manager chiederanno scusa|last=Pica|first=Paola|work=Corriere della Sera|access-date=18 August 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref> The M5S asked the revocation of license to Benetton family and the [[nationalization]] of Autostrade per l'Italia.<ref>[https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html Autostrade, via alla revoca delle concessioni. Di Maio: 'Benetton perderanno profitti'], ANSA</ref> However, despite bitter controversies, the revocation has not yet been implemented.\n\nThe last two cable-stayed pillars of the bridge were demolished [[explosive demolition|using a tonne of explosives]] on 28 June 2019. The complete bridge was planned to be removed, along with multiple damaged houses in the surrounding area.<ref name=bbc-20190628>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |title=Morandi bridge towers demolished in Genoa |work=BBC News |date=28 June 2019 |accessdate=28 June 2019}}</ref> A replacement bridge, designed by Italian architect [[Renzo Piano]], has been under construction since 25 June 2019, and is set to be opened in the first half of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|title=After Bridge Tragedy, Genoa Selects a New Design|date=2019-01-10|website=www.engineering.com|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Constitutional reform===\nUnder Conte's governments, the [[Italian Parliament]] approved the so-called \"[[Riccardo Fraccaro|Fraccaro]] Reform\", from the name of the M5S deputy who was the bill's first signatory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|title=La Camera approva la riforma Fraccaro. Via al taglio dei parlamentari - TGR Trento|website=TGR}}</ref> The reform was finally approved by the Parliament, with the fourth and final vote in the Chamber of Deputies on 8 October with 553 votes in favor and 14 against. In the final vote, the bill was supported both by the majority and the opposition;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sciorilli Borrelli |first1=Silvia |title=Italian lawmakers want fewer Italian lawmakers |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=8 October 2019}}</ref> only the liberal party [[More Europe]] (+Eu) and other small groups voted against.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|title=Taglio dei parlamentari, Orfini: \"La riforma fa schifo\". Chi sono i contrari|website=it.notizie.yahoo.com}}</ref> The reform provided a cut in the number of MPs, which would shrink from 630 to 400 deputies and from 315 to 200 senators.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy shrinks parliament 'to save \u20ac1bn' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=BBC News |date=8 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter the approval, Conte stated: \"The cut to the parliamentarians is a reform that will bring to a greater efficiency of the parliamentary jobs. Now, citizens to be closer to the institutions. It is a historical passage that, together with other projected reform, will be a prelude to greater efficiency of our parliamentary system.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|title=Taglio parlamentari \u00e8 legge: Montecitorio approva con 553 S\u00ec. Di Maio: \"Fatto storico, saremo leali su contrappesi\". Conte: \"Riforma riduce i costi e dar\u00e0 pi\u00f9 efficienza\"|date=8 October 2019|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2020 Italian constitutional referendum|referendum]] to approve the reform was scheduled on 29 March, however it was postponed due to the [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Italy.<ref>[https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari inviato il referendum del 29 marzo sul taglio dei parlamentari]</ref>\n\n===Coronavirus pandemic===\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Italian [[Conte II Cabinet|government]] task force to face the coronavirus pandemic]]\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy}}\nIn February 2020, Italy became the first European country and the second in the world for confirmed cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], a virus from [[China]] which caused a respiratory disease.<ref>[https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html Coronavirus, Italia prima in Europa per numero di contagi: \u00e8 caccia ai focolai]</ref> In late January, the government banned all flights from and to China, becoming the first European country to adopt this measure.<ref>[https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ Coronavirus, primi due casi confermati in Italia: sono turisti cinesi a Roma. Chiuso il traffico aereo con la Cina]</ref> In February and March, over 60,000 coronavirus cases were confirmed, affecting mainly [[Lombardy]], [[Emilia-Romagna]] and [[Veneto]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano|last=online|first=Simona Ravizza e redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Council of Ministers]] announced a bill to contain the COVID-19 outbreak, quarantining more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. Prime Minister Conte stated: \"In the outbreak areas, entry and exit will not be provided. Suspension of work activities and sport events has already been ordered in those areas.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/decreto_governo_contro_coronavirus-249308355/|title=Coronavirus, decreto del governo: nei comuni focolaio stop ad ingressi ed uscite. Conte: \"Non trasformeremo l'Italia in un lazzaretto\"|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in 10 municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and in Emilia-Romagna. In some areas, all public events were cancelled and commercial activities were halted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-21|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Regional train services suspended the stops in the most affected areas \u2013 with trains not stopping at Codogno, Maleo and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy suspended all activities from 23 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all\u20191/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=www.unimi.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo|website=www.unibg.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2020, Prime Minister Conte extended the quarantine to all of [[Lombardy]] and 14 other northern provinces, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|putting more than a quarter of the national population under lockdown]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On the following day, he announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting ''de facto'' 60 million people in lockdown. He later proceeded to officially sign the executive decree.<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise]</ref><ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country]</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in human history.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html On Day 1 of Broad Lockdown, a Debate Arises: Can Italians Follow the Rules?]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country\u2019s North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html|accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan], ''[[Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nThe lockdown measures, despite being widely approved by [[public opinion]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=De Feo |first1=Gianluca |title=Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle |url=https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |website=YouTrend |accessdate=22 March 2020 |language=it-IT |date=20 March 2020}}</ref> were also described as the largest suppression of [[constitutional right]]s in the history of the republic.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blog {{!}} Coronavirus, la sospensione delle libert\u00e0 costituzionali \u00e8 realt\u00e0. Ma per me ce la stiamo cavando bene |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=18 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Un uomo solo \u00e8 al comando dell\u2019Italia, e nessuno ha niente da ridire|url=https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Linkiesta |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence.  Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref> While on the following day, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=ilmessaggero.it |language=it}}</ref> following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, Conte's government extended the period of lockdown until 13 April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |title=Italy extends lockdown amid signs coronavirus infection rate is easing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n{{See also|List of official trips made by Giuseppe Conte}}\n[[File:President Trump Meets with the Prime Minister of the Italian Republic (49173499077).jpg|thumb|Conte with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] in December 2019]]\nSince the beginning of his term as prime minister, Conte's [[foreign policy]] has been characterized by a lenient approach to Russia. For example, he advocated the repeal of international sanctions against Russia, which according to him damage the [[Italian economy]].<ref>[https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml Putin a Roma, Conte contro le sanzioni a Mosca: \"Sono un danno per tutti\"], TgCom24</ref> He also considered Russia a strategic partner in the [[War on Terror|fight]] against [[Islamic terrorism]].<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|title=Conte: appartenenza alla Nato ma apriremo alla Russia|agency=[[ASCA (news agency)|ASCA]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, Conte stressed that under his leadership Italy will remain an active member of [[NATO]] and a close ally of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|title=Conte: restiamo nella Nato e con Usa ma via sanzioni alla Russia|language=it|date=5 July 2018|trans-title=Conte: We remain in NATO and with the USA but via sanctions against Russia|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 and 9 June, Conte participated in his first [[44th G7 summit|G7 summit]], hosted by Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|title=G7, il primo incontro del premier Conte con gli altri leader. FOTO - Sky TG24|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> During the summit, he was the only leader to back U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and his proposal to readmit Russia into the G7.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Reuters|date=8 June 2018|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|title=Italy's new PM backs Trump on re-admitting Russia into the G7|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> However, he later assumed a more [[pro-Europe]]an view, shared by the other five leaders, condemning [[Trump tariffs]] on [[steel]] and [[aluminium]] exported by the [[European Union]].<ref>{{cite news|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|title=G7, Trudeau: \"Documento finale firmato da tutti\". Trump va via e chiede riammissione Russia|work=la Repubblica|language=it}}</ref> On the following day, Conte was thanked for his positions on Russia and his populist stance by President Trump, who invited him to the [[White House]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|title=Trump: Italy's populist prime minister to visit White House|author=Brent D. Griffiths|website=[[Politico]]|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> After a few days, Trump praised Conte, describing him as a \"really great\" leader and \"very strong on immigration\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|title=Trump: \"Il primo ministro italiano Conte \u00e8 fantastico. \u00c8 severo sull'immigrazione e in questo momento paga\"|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Trump endorsed Conte during the [[2019 Italian government formation#Political crisis|2019 Italian political crisis]], hoping that he could remain Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|title=L'endorsement di Trump per il Conte-bis|website=Agi}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 June, Conte participated in his first [[European Council]] meeting and blocked a joint EU trade and defense statement criticizing Trump's tariff policy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|title=Italy blocks joint text on trade, defense at EU summit|date=28 June 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48616362963).jpg|thumb|left|Conte and other leaders at the [[45th G7 summit]] in Biarritz, France]]\nIn March 2019, Conte and the Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] [[2019 Xi Jinping Italy and France visit|signed in Rome]] 29 economic and institutional agreements amounting to 2.5 billion [[euro]]s, including a [[memorandum of understanding]] vis-\u00e0-vis the [[Belt and Road Initiative]] investments program.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|title=Cina-Italia, firmati gli accordi. Di Maio: \"Valgono 2,5 miliardi ma con un potenziale di 20\". Gelo con Salvini|work=la Repubblica}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|title=Xi Jinping a Roma, firmato il Memorandum su Via della Seta. \"Grazie Italia, un successo\"|publisher=QuotidianoNet|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> In August 2019, he took part, as caretaker Prime Minister, in the [[45th G7 summit]] in [[Biarritz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|title=Conte resiste nel 'fortino dorato' di Biarritz (da Biarritz A. Mauro)|date=25 August 2019|website=L'HuffPost}}</ref> The main topics of the summit included [[global trade]], [[climate change]], taxing technology companies,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |title=Trump Arrives in Biarritz for Testing G7 Summit |date=24 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> but also [[Iran nuclear deal]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |title=G7 Summit to Be 'a Difficult Test of Unity': EU's Tusk |date=24 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref> and [[2019 Amazon wildfires]].<ref name=\"theguardian_Phillips_20190822\">{{Cite news| issn = 0261-3077| last1 = Phillips| first1 = Tom| last2 = correspondent| first2 = Latin America| title = Amazon rainforest fires: Macron calls for 'international crisis' to lead G7 discussions| work = The Guardian| access-date = 23 August 2019| date = 23 August 2019| url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions}}</ref>\n\nConte criticized the [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria]]. He stated that the offensive puts the region's civilians and stability in jeopardy.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html \"World reacts to Turkey's military operation in northeast Syria\"]. Al Jazeera. 10 October 2019.</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the situation of the [[Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)|Libyan Civil War]] became increasingly worrying, with the troops of field marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]] approaching [[Tripoli]]. During the crisis, Prime Minister Conte had a series of bilateral meetings in Rome both with Haftar and [[Fayez al-Sarraj]], the Chairman of the [[Presidential Council (Libya)|Presidential Council of Libya]], who are considered two of the main contenders in the civil war.<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB Libia, Haftar annuncia il cessate il fuoco. L\u2019incontro Conte-Sarraj]</ref> After pressures from the international community, on 12 January Haftar announced a [[ceasefire]].<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html Libyan forces loyal to Haftar announce conditional ceasefire]</ref>\n\nOn 22 March 2020, after a phone call with Conte, Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the [[Russian Armed Forces|Russian army]] to send military medics, special disinfection vehicles and other medical equipment to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Political views==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte August 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Giuseppe Conte with troops in 2019]]\nDuring an interview in 2018, Conte said he used to vote for the [[Left-wing politics|left]] before approaching the M5S during the late 2010s. He also added that today \"the ideological schemes of the 20th century are no longer adequate to represent the current [[political system]]\" and it should be \"more important and correct to evaluate the work of a political force on how it is positioned on the respect of fundamental [[Human rights|rights]] and freedoms\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|title=Giuseppe Conte, ecco chi \u00e8 il presidente del consiglio del governo Lega-M5s|date=31 May 2018|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn his inaugural speech at the Senate on 5 June 2018,<ref name=\"rep_050618\">{{cite web|title=Il discorso di Conte in Senato, la versione integrale|url=http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Dichiarazioni programmatiche - L'intervento del Presidente Conte al Senato|medium=official video|language=it|url=http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|publisher=Governo Italiano - Presidenza del Consiglio dei Ministri}}</ref> in response to attacks on government political forces accused of being populist and [[anti-establishment]], Conte replied that \"if populism is the attitude of the ruling class to listen to the people's needs [...] and if anti-establishment means aiming at introducing a new system able to remove old privileges and encrusted power, well, these political forces deserve both these epithets\".<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html \"Italy's New Populist Government Articulates Vision, but Few Specifics\"].</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Highlights: Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte's inaugural speech|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Conte: \"Noi populisti? Ascoltiamo la gente|medium=video|language=Italian|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|work=[[il Giornale]]}}</ref>\n\nHe also opposed the \"hypertrophy of Italian laws\", advocating the repeal of useless laws and supported a simplification of [[bureaucracy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|date=21 May 2018|author=Diodato Pirone|title=Conte, giurista anti-burocrazia con un passato a sinistra|trans-title=Conte, former anti-bureaucracy lawyer joins the left|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Conte strongly opposed the [[school reform]] legislation promoted by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2015, known as \"The Good School\", which he said must be completely revised.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|title=Giuseppe Conte: rivedere, pressoch\u00e9 integralmente, la riforma della cattiva scuola|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte, a [[Roman Catholic]], is a devout votary to [[Padre Pio|Padre Pio of Pietrelcina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|title=Devoto di Padre Pio, secchione e di sinistra. Il \"Financial Times\" lo stronca: un novellino|work=il Giornale|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Despite being labeled as a post-ideological leader,<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/in-edicola/articoli/2019/09/20/dalema-benedice-il-nuovo-conte-post-ideologico-tra-selfie-e-salsicce/5465121/ D\u2019Alema benedice il nuovo Conte post-ideologico, tra selfie e salsicce], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref> Conte described his political ideal as \"new [[Renaissance humanism|humanism]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|title=Conte: \"Mondo non-pi\u00f9 eurocentrico, Italia per nuovo umanesimo\"|website=Adnkronos}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|title=Il testo completo del discorso di Giuseppe Conte al Senato|website=Fanpage}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGiuseppe Conte married Valentina Fico, a lawyer from [[Rome]] and daughter of a former director of the Santa Cecilia [[music school|conservatory]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|title=Valentina Fico, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|first=Olga|last=Luce|date=29 August 2019|website=Donne Magazine}}</ref> They have a child, Niccol\u00f2, born in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|title=Giuseppe Conte, chi \u00e8 il professore (di sinistra) che potrebbe diventare premier|date=21 May 2018}}</ref> However, they divorced after a few years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-l-ex-moglie-di-Giuseppe-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> Conte is currently engaged with Olivia Paladino (born 1979),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-Olivia-Paladino-l-affascinante-fidanzata-del-premier-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, l'affascinante fidanzata del premier Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> daughter of the Roman entrepreneur Cesare Paladino and the [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress [[Ewa Aulin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|title=Chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, la compagna del premier Giuseppe Conte - LetteraDonna}}</ref>\n\nConte is an avid supporter of [[A.S. Roma]], a passion that arose when he studied in [[Rome]] at the Sapienza University.<ref>[https://www.tpi.it/news/giuseppe-conte-squadra-calcio-20180606128675/ Quali sono le squadre del cuore di Giuseppe Conte e degli ex premier italiani], TPI</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Quirinale 2019.jpg|thumb|220px|Giuseppe Conte in August 2019]]\nOn 21 May 2018, when Conte was proposed to President Mattarella as candidate for prime minister,<ref name=bbc/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' questioned his summer stays at [[New York University]] (NYU) listed in his official [[curriculum vitae]]<ref name=cv/> in an article asserting that a NYU spokeswoman could not find Conte in university \"records as either a student or faculty member\".<ref name=nyt/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|title=Giuseppe Conte, Nyt: \"Nel cv studi alla New York University che non-risultano all'ateneo\". Accademici: \"Visiting scholar non-sono registrati\"|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|date=22 May 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similar doubts arose concerning his study period in France at the [[Sorbonne University]].<ref name=theguardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|title=Doubts raised over academic credentials of proposed Italian PM|author=Kirchgaessner, Stephanie|author2=Giuffrida, Angela|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the [[Associated Press]] reported in an article published also by ''The New York Times'' that the NYU spokeswoman added that \"while Mr. Conte had no official status at NYU, he was granted permission to conduct research in the NYU law library\" during the period listed in his official curriculum vitae.<ref name=cv/><ref>{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|agency=Associated Press|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}<br />{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/05/22/world/europe/ap-eu-italy-politics-the-latest.html|work=The New York Times|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similarly, the [[Duquesne University]] of [[Pittsburgh]] and the [[University of Malta]] found no record of him in their archives,<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lorenzo De Cicco|author2=Francesca Pierantozzi|author3=Flavio Pompetti|date=22 May 2018|title=Conte, dopo New York anche le universit\u00e0 di Malta e Pittsburgh: \"Non ha mai studiato o insegnato ufficialmente qui\"|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|work=Il Messaggero|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> although it was confirmed that Conte held lectures at the old university building in [[Valletta]], Malta, for the Foundation for International Studies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|title=Italian prime minister candidate says he lectured in Malta - but the University has no record of him|newspaper=Times of Malta|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> [[Yale University]], contacted by another newspaper, confirmed that he was a visiting scholar there for three months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|title=Conte e il curriculum, Yale conferma: \"Visiting scholar per tre mesi\"|author=Sarcina, Giuseppe|work=Corriere della Sera|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nMoreover, Conte stated in his CV that he had worked for his legal studies at the Kulturinstitut in [[Vienna]], Austria, but this is a language school, not a law school.<ref name=theguardian/>\n\n==Authored books==\n*{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gpBBDwAAQBAJ|title=Il volontariato. Libert\u00e0 dei privati e mediazione giuridica dello Stato|last=Conte|first=Giuseppe|last2=Landini|first2=Sara|year=1996|isbn=9788899459772|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|author-mask=with}}\n*{{cite book|title=Matrimonio civile e teoria della simulazione|year=1996|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|oclc=1088868085}}\n*{{cite book|title=La simulazione del matrimonio nella teoria del negozio giuridico|year=1999|isbn=9788813220068|publisher=CEDAM|location=[[Padua]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Le regole della solidarit\u00e0. Iniziative non-profit dei privati e mediazione dei pubblici poteri|year=2001|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Il danno non-patrimoniale|year=2018|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=La formazione del contratto|year=2018|isbn=9788814203770|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=L'impresa responsabile|year=2018|isbn=9788814227035|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*University of Florence [https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html personal page] (including CV and publication list in English)\n*{{Scopus id}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paolo Gentiloni]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Italy]]|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|italy}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Roberto Fico]]|as=[[List of Presidents of the Italian Chamber of Deputies|President of the Chamber of Deputies]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Italian order of precedence|Order of precedence of Italy]]<br />''{{small|as Prime Minister}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marta Cartabia]]<br />''{{small|{{nowrap|as [[Constitutional Court of Italy|President of the Constitutional Court]]}}}}''}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Prime Ministers of Italy}}\n{{Offices of italy}}\n{{European Council}}\n{{Current NATO leaders}}\n{{Current G8 Leaders}}\n{{Current G20 Leaders}}\n{{Conte I Cabinet}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Giuseppe}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Conte I Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Italian jurists]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Foggia]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Roma Tre University faculty]]\n[[Category:Sapienza University of Rome alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Florence faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Malta faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Sassari faculty]]\n[[Category:Yale Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in Italy]]\n", "name_user": "5.90.41.168", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giuseppe_Conte"}
{"title_page": "Tor Carding Forum", "text_new": "{{Infobox website\n| name = https://altenens.org\n| logo = Tor Carding Forums logo.png\n| logo_size = \n| logocaption = \n| screenshot = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = \n| collapsetext = \n| url = <!-- independent source required -->\n| commercial = \n| type = [[Internet forum]]\n| registration = https://altenens.org\n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| num_users = \n| content_license = \n| owner = \n| author = \n| editor = \n| launch_date = \n| revenue = \n| alexa = \n| current_status = Unknown\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\nThe '''Tor Carding Forum''' (TCF) was a [[Tor (anonymity network)|Tor]]-based [[Internet forum|forum]] specializing in the trade of [[Carding (fraud)|stolen credit card]] details, [[identity theft]] and [[Counterfeit money|currency counterfeiting]]. The site was founded by an individual known as 'Verto' who also founded the now defunct [[Evolution (marketplace)|Evolution]] [[darknet market]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wired Staff|title=The Most Dangerous People on the Internet Right Now|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/01/dangerous-people-internet-right-now/|accessdate=1 August 2015|date=1 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe site required $50 for registration.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kiell|title=A Carder\u2019s First Experience|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/12/11/a-carders-first-experience/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=11 December 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418111640/http://www.validmarket.io/2014/12/11/a-carders-first-experience/|archive-date=18 April 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Greenberg|first1=Andy|title=The Dark Web Gets Darker With Rise of the \u2018Evolution\u2019 Drug Market|url=https://www.wired.com/2014/09/dark-web-evolution/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=18 September 2014}}</ref>\n\nA 2013 investigation into counterfeit banknotes in [[Pittsburgh]] led to a source of [[Uganda]]n fakes being identified as having been purchased via the Tor Carding Forums.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rohrlich|first1=Justin|title=The Counterfeiting Missionary and the Fake Pittsburgh Playboy|url=https://news.vice.com/article/the-counterfeiting-missionary-and-the-fake-pittsburgh-playboy|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=27 January 2015}}</ref> By December 2014 Ryan Andrew Gustafson a.k.a. \"Jack Farrel\" and \"Willy Clock\", a US citizen living in Uganda was arrested for large scale sale of counterfeit [[Counterfeit United States currency|United States currency]] by the [[U.S. Secret Service]] which was being sold through the Tor Carding Forums as well as other [[crime forum]]s.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krebs|first1=Brian|title=Alleged Counterfeiter \"Willy Clock\" Arrested|url=http://krebsonsecurity.com/2014/12/alleged-counterfeiter-willy-clock-arrested/|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014 the site closed following a hack, directing users to Evolution's forums.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Farivar|first1=Cyrus|title=After Silk Road takedowns, Dark Web drug sites still thriving|url=https://arstechnica.com/business/2014/12/after-two-silk-road-takedowns-dark-web-drug-sites-still-thriving/|accessdate=1 August 2015|date=19 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=DeepDotWeb|title=Evolution Marketplace Staff Speak: We are growing fast!|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/05/10/evolution-marketplace-staff-speak-we-are-growing-fast/|accessdate=16 August 2015|date=10 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008053727/https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/05/10/evolution-marketplace-staff-speak-we-are-growing-fast/|archive-date=8 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2015 a [[dark web]] researcher identified the [[clearnet (networking)|clearnet]] IP address of a similar hidden service branded 'The Tor Carding Forum V2'<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cox|first1=Joseph|title=This Researcher Is Hunting Down IP Addresses of Dark Web Sites|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/this-researcher-is-hunting-down-ip-addresses-of-dark-web-sites|accessdate=31 July 2015|date=22 June 2015}}</ref> which was subsequently shut down.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Guthrie Weissman|first1=Cale|title=The dark web is growing but people have already figured out how to track down its most hidden websites|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/dark-web-researcher-discovers-ip-addresses-in-plain-sight-2015-6?r=US&IR=T|accessdate=8 December 2015|date=23 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Tor hidden services}}\n[[Category:Internet forums]]\n[[Category:Cybercrime]]\n[[Category:Defunct Tor hidden services|Carding]]\n[[Category:Crime forums]]\n[[Category:Carding (fraud)]]\n{{crime-stub}}\n{{Internet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox website\n| name = Tor Carding Forum\n| logo = Tor Carding Forums logo.png\n| logo_size = \n| logocaption = \n| screenshot = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = \n| collapsetext = \n| url = <!-- independent source required -->\n| commercial = \n| type = [[Internet forum]]\n| registration = \n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| num_users = \n| content_license = \n| owner = \n| author = \n| editor = \n| launch_date = \n| revenue = \n| alexa = \n| current_status = Unknown\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\nThe '''Tor Carding Forum''' (TCF) was a [[Tor (anonymity network)|Tor]]-based [[Internet forum|forum]] specializing in the trade of [[Carding (fraud)|stolen credit card]] details, [[identity theft]] and [[Counterfeit money|currency counterfeiting]]. The site was founded by an individual known as 'Verto' who also founded the now defunct [[Evolution (marketplace)|Evolution]] [[darknet market]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wired Staff|title=The Most Dangerous People on the Internet Right Now|url=https://www.wired.com/2015/01/dangerous-people-internet-right-now/|accessdate=1 August 2015|date=1 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe site required $50 for registration.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kiell|title=A Carder\u2019s First Experience|url=https://www.deepdotweb.com/2014/12/11/a-carders-first-experience/|acce